1
00:00:00,033 --> 00:00:03,337
[Bonjour Bakery]

2
00:00:03,337 --> 00:00:07,074
[Day 2 Morning]

3
00:00:07,708 --> 00:00:09,610
Should we go pick up the strawberries?

4
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:12,179
- Let's go.
- Okay.

5
00:00:13,514 --> 00:00:16,583
It's such a pretty café.

6
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:20,454
[People Keep Passing By As A New Day Begins]

7
00:00:29,496 --> 00:00:31,098
Good morning.

8
00:00:33,634 --> 00:00:34,835
Our café just opened.

9
00:00:34,835 --> 00:00:36,937
We open at 11 a.m.

10
00:00:36,937 --> 00:00:38,338
- What?
- This café.

11
00:00:38,338 --> 00:00:40,474
- I see.
- Do you like coffee?

12
00:00:40,474 --> 00:00:42,075
I had some yesterday.

13
00:00:42,075 --> 00:00:43,777
Did you come by yesterday?

14
00:00:43,777 --> 00:00:45,445
Today's coffee tastes different.

15
00:00:45,445 --> 00:00:47,014
Because I'm here today.

16
00:00:47,014 --> 00:00:48,415
- I wasn't here yesterday.
- Right.

17
00:00:48,415 --> 00:00:50,551
I had to go somewhere,
and I just got back today.

18
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:53,420
- What's your name?
- My name is Kim Seon Ho.

19
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:54,721
- Is that right?
- Yes.

20
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:55,656
- Have a nice day.
- Okay.

21
00:00:55,656 --> 00:00:57,257
If you get a chance later,

22
00:00:57,257 --> 00:00:58,825
- come by again.
- Okay.

23
00:00:58,825 --> 00:00:59,993
- All right.
- Bye.

24
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,329
- Thank you.
- Bye.

25
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:07,067
[Good Mood, Good Weather]

26
00:01:07,734 --> 00:01:11,405
[A Great Day To Work]

27
00:01:11,405 --> 00:01:12,739
Let's go.

28
00:01:15,475 --> 00:01:21,148
[Setting Off To Get Strawberries For Today's Menu]

29
00:01:23,617 --> 00:01:25,886
The weather is so nice today.

30
00:01:25,886 --> 00:01:27,821
- It is.
- Right?

31
00:01:27,821 --> 00:01:31,391
Do you prefer mountains or the ocean?

32
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:33,527
I personally like both,

33
00:01:33,527 --> 00:01:35,762
but nowadays,

34
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:38,665
I enjoy seeing grass and mountains.

35
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:40,167
- Nowadays.
- A green horizon.

36
00:01:40,167 --> 00:01:42,169
I think my tastes keep changing.

37
00:01:42,169 --> 00:01:44,171
Not because of age.

38
00:01:44,171 --> 00:01:45,639
It keeps changing, just like trends.

39
00:01:45,639 --> 00:01:47,174
- What about you?
- For me...

40
00:01:49,676 --> 00:01:53,146
[Looks Over]

41
00:01:53,146 --> 00:01:55,983
More than the ocean,
when I see fields and mountains,

42
00:01:55,983 --> 00:01:58,285
- that kind of green landscape,
- Yes?

43
00:01:58,285 --> 00:02:00,354
[I'm With You If You Like It]
I feel a sense of peace.

44
00:02:00,354 --> 00:02:05,025
Didn't you do car stunts in The Tyrant?

45
00:02:05,892 --> 00:02:08,795
- It was so awesome.
- I guess that means you saw it.

46
00:02:08,795 --> 00:02:11,198
I think I've seen most of your works.

47
00:02:11,198 --> 00:02:13,470
I've seen nearly all of them.

48
00:02:15,202 --> 00:02:17,671
[Time Passes Quickly While Chatting]

49
00:02:17,671 --> 00:02:20,741
[Before They Know It
They're At The Strawberry Farm]

50
00:02:22,609 --> 00:02:25,112
Oh, so this is the place.

51
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:28,649
- Hello.
- Hello.

52
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:30,817
- Hello.
- We're from Bonjour Bakery.

53
00:02:30,817 --> 00:02:33,086
- We came to pick up the strawberries.
- Welcome.

54
00:02:34,388 --> 00:02:35,656
They're so pretty.

55
00:02:36,323 --> 00:02:38,258
Wow, they look amazing.

56
00:02:39,192 --> 00:02:42,929
[Sun-Soaked Well-Ripened Strawberries]

57
00:02:43,530 --> 00:02:47,801
[What Dessert Will Be Made
With These Freshly-Picked Strawberries? ]

58
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:48,969
Would you like to try one?

59
00:02:48,969 --> 00:02:51,071
- Can we pick one off the vine?
- Yes.

60
00:03:01,048 --> 00:03:02,849
It's delicious.

61
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:04,720
It's the sweetest strawberry
I've had in a while.

62
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,779
It's so good.

63
00:03:05,779 --> 00:03:07,281
- It's so sweet, right?
- Yes.

64
00:03:14,294 --> 00:03:15,796
It's so tasty.

65
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:18,065
Can I just have one more?

66
00:03:18,065 --> 00:03:19,266
Yes, help yourself.

67
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:25,706
- Oh, it's a Seolhyang strawberry.
- That's right.

68
00:03:25,706 --> 00:03:27,207
Why is it called "Seolhyang"?

69
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:30,877
They say you eat strawberries
when the first snow falls,

70
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,479
and "seol" means "snow."

71
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:33,780
[They Grow In Snow From November To Spring]

72
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:35,782
They were developed in Nonsan,

73
00:03:35,782 --> 00:03:37,319
so they're domestic.

74
00:03:38,151 --> 00:03:39,386
Let's push them in as we go.

75
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,054
- Okay.
- Just load it there for now.

76
00:03:42,189 --> 00:03:46,827
[Gochang Strawberries]

77
00:03:46,827 --> 00:03:48,161
They smell so good.

78
00:04:01,842 --> 00:04:03,076
Thank you!

79
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,411
Thank you.

80
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:11,351
[Heading Back To The Bakery
With The Fragrant Strawberries]

81
00:04:11,351 --> 00:04:14,888
[Bonjour Bakery]

82
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:18,965
[Chef Cha Is Ready To Get To Work]

83
00:04:18,965 --> 00:04:20,757
Oh, there's a mirror here.

84
00:04:34,474 --> 00:04:38,211
[Taking Out The Brioche Dough
That Was Left To Rise Overnight]

85
00:04:38,211 --> 00:04:43,984
[Takes Out The Brioche Dough
From The Retarder-Proofer]

86
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:57,631
[Apply Egg Wash To The Proofed Dough]

87
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:03,904
[The Key Is To Brush It On Evenly]

88
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:14,381
[Top The Egg-Washed Dough
With Green Barley Sablé]

89
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:32,065
[Ready To Place Inside The Oven]

90
00:05:36,036 --> 00:05:39,840
[Bake In The Oven
At 150 Degrees For 15 Minutes]

91
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,563
I'll make three trays.

92
00:05:48,281 --> 00:05:50,083
We're back.

93
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:51,685
Good morning, Seung Won.

94
00:05:51,685 --> 00:05:52,886
You're busy.

95
00:05:52,886 --> 00:05:54,721
We brought the strawberries.

96
00:05:54,721 --> 00:05:57,691
[Too Busy Focusing To Greet Them]

97
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:01,795
[Now That The Strawberries
Have Been Delivered]

98
00:06:01,795 --> 00:06:06,700
[It's Time For Seon Ho To Put On
His Uniform And Get To Work]

99
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:45,205
[Crunchy Green Barley Sablé]

100
00:06:45,205 --> 00:06:49,609
[Atop Soft And Tender Bread]

101
00:06:50,443 --> 00:06:54,547
[Make A Hole To Fill The Bread
With Green Barley Cream]

102
00:07:01,154 --> 00:07:05,358
[Then Add Gochang Green Barley Cream]

103
00:07:10,964 --> 00:07:12,432
[Savory On The Outside, Sweet On The Inside]

104
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:15,435
[Green Barley Brioche Complete!]

105
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:20,140
Green Barley Grioche.

106
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:22,242
[Green Barley Brioche]

107
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:30,750
[The Manager Is Heading To Work]

108
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,411
She looks so youthful and feminine today.

109
00:07:39,359 --> 00:07:41,261
- Welcome, come on in.
- Oh, my.

110
00:07:41,261 --> 00:07:42,595
Look who it is.

111
00:07:42,595 --> 00:07:43,930
- Welcome back.
- Was everything okay?

112
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:45,532
- Let's do this.
- Good to have you back.

113
00:07:45,532 --> 00:07:47,505
I feel today will go smoothly now.

114
00:07:48,068 --> 00:07:49,636
[Popping Into The Kitchen To Say Hello]
Hello.

115
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,604
- Hi, Hee Ae.
- Good morning.

116
00:07:52,939 --> 00:07:55,742
It must hurt your back to hunch over
since you're so tall.

117
00:07:55,742 --> 00:07:56,876
No, it's okay.

118
00:07:56,876 --> 00:07:59,679
[Hunched]

119
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:01,881
[Prepping For The Day]
The clock...

120
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:03,616
- I'll leave this here, Hee Ae.
- Okay.

121
00:08:03,616 --> 00:08:05,852
[Making Sure She Has Her Hygiene Mask]

122
00:08:09,856 --> 00:08:12,625
Is this right?

123
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:13,960
No?

124
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,628
Oh, it's upside down?

125
00:08:17,097 --> 00:08:18,598
That's so funny.

126
00:08:21,434 --> 00:08:23,218
How's it going here?

127
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:25,739
Today's menu includes éclairs.

128
00:08:25,739 --> 00:08:27,540
- Okay.
- Today's special is éclairs.

129
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:28,663
- Éclairs.
- How exciting.

130
00:08:28,663 --> 00:08:31,378
We'll also serve the Green Barley...

131
00:08:31,378 --> 00:08:34,381
The Crème Brûlée is ready,
and so's the Sweet Potato Cake.

132
00:08:34,381 --> 00:08:37,283
I got all the ingredients ready
for the strawberry and blueberry éclairs,

133
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:39,182
so I just need to make them.

134
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:43,223
- Seung Won.
- Yes?

135
00:08:43,223 --> 00:08:45,158
- You were so sexy just now.
- Why?

136
00:08:45,158 --> 00:08:46,659
- You're so cool.
- Come on.

137
00:08:46,659 --> 00:08:48,658
- Really.
- That's all that's left to do.

138
00:08:52,532 --> 00:08:53,533
Are you feeling okay?

139
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,402
- Yes.
- Good.

140
00:08:55,402 --> 00:08:58,171
I'm feeling great.

141
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:03,510
[Before Opening]

142
00:09:04,744 --> 00:09:06,413
[Before The Café Opens]

143
00:09:06,413 --> 00:09:07,647
Brûlée...

144
00:09:07,647 --> 00:09:10,383
[He Writes Down Everything On Today's Menu]

145
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:11,785
Next...

146
00:09:23,029 --> 00:09:26,099
[Today's Menu]

147
00:09:26,566 --> 00:09:29,769
[Bonjour Strawberry Éclair]

148
00:09:29,769 --> 00:09:33,339
[Bonjour Blueberry Éclair]

149
00:09:33,339 --> 00:09:36,142
[Bonjour Green Barley Tart]

150
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:39,913
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Cake]

151
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:41,714
[Bonjour Crème Brûlée]

152
00:09:41,714 --> 00:09:45,919
[Bonjour Green Barley Brioche]

153
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:47,987
[Bonjour Bokbunja Madeleine]

154
00:09:47,987 --> 00:09:49,689
[Bonjour Citron Madeleine And Financier]

155
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:58,331
[10:42 a.m.]

156
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:01,534
[18 Minutes Before Opening]

157
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:06,172
[Making Desserts Made Us Realize]

158
00:10:08,241 --> 00:10:12,512
[That Cake Cutting Is Also An Art]

159
00:10:15,415 --> 00:10:18,218
[Behind The Scenes
Cutting Sweet Potato Cake Into 5 Pieces]

160
00:10:41,741 --> 00:10:43,610
[Glaze]

161
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:53,219
It's here.

162
00:11:00,226 --> 00:11:03,263
[10:55 a.m. Finals Checks Before Opening]

163
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:10,003
Would it be okay to use this plate?

164
00:11:10,003 --> 00:11:12,205
- This one seems a little small.
- Okay.

165
00:11:14,407 --> 00:11:16,009
[Flustered]

166
00:11:20,713 --> 00:11:22,549
I'm so sorry.

167
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:30,723
[Makes A Mistake]

168
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:32,526
Turn off the camera.

169
00:11:33,226 --> 00:11:34,294
Cover that one with a towel.

170
00:11:34,294 --> 00:11:36,103
I'm really sorry, Seung Won.

171
00:11:37,564 --> 00:11:40,400
[11 a.m. Day 2, Open For Business]

172
00:11:41,134 --> 00:11:42,468
All right.

173
00:11:53,746 --> 00:11:56,749
Where is everyone?

174
00:11:56,749 --> 00:12:00,587
Shouldn't there be a huge line here?

175
00:12:00,587 --> 00:12:01,921
Where's everyone gone?

176
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:04,857
We're open!

177
00:12:04,857 --> 00:12:07,293
Just wait. It will get hectic in a bit.

178
00:12:07,293 --> 00:12:08,461
Be patient.

179
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:12,799
I was just like you yesterday.

180
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:14,200
"Why aren't there any people around?"

181
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,468
"Why is no one coming?"

182
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:17,403
But you shouldn't say, "It's so quiet."

183
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:20,506
[Because Then It Gets Really Busy]

184
00:12:23,943 --> 00:12:27,680
Grandpa, this place is only open
to people over 65 years old.

185
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:31,584
They're here.

186
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:32,952
[Someone's Here!]

187
00:12:37,023 --> 00:12:38,024
Hello.

188
00:12:38,024 --> 00:12:40,059
- Hello.
- Hello.

189
00:12:40,059 --> 00:12:41,661
I hope you won't mind,

190
00:12:41,661 --> 00:12:43,563
- but can I check your ID?
- Of course.

191
00:12:43,563 --> 00:12:45,707
- Our bakery...
- You need to show your ID.

192
00:12:50,837 --> 00:12:52,038
Thank you.

193
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:56,476
All right, then.

194
00:12:56,476 --> 00:12:58,144
Why don't you sit over here?

195
00:12:58,144 --> 00:12:59,045
[Today's First Customers]

196
00:12:59,045 --> 00:13:00,847
- Is this table okay?
- Yes.

197
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:03,850
- You sit there.
- Take a seat, Grandpa.

198
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:06,853
[A Senior Gentleman
And His Two Grown Granddaughters]

199
00:13:09,555 --> 00:13:11,658
You managed to get here

200
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:13,826
- as soon as we opened.
- Yes.

201
00:13:15,061 --> 00:13:17,630
- This here is a wet towel.
- Okay.

202
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:20,967
- Use it now while it's still warm.
- Okay.

203
00:13:22,635 --> 00:13:24,704
Grandpa has never been to a café before.

204
00:13:24,704 --> 00:13:26,639
- Really?
- Yes, it's his first time.

205
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,475
- Does he drink coffee?
- He does.

206
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:31,944
- But he's only had instant coffee.
- Sweet coffee.

207
00:13:31,944 --> 00:13:33,413
Then how about a vanilla latte?

208
00:13:33,413 --> 00:13:35,815
It's warm and sweet like instant coffee.

209
00:13:35,815 --> 00:13:37,383
For today's morning menu,

210
00:13:37,383 --> 00:13:40,119
- we have Bonjour Blueberry Éclairs
- It looks so good.

211
00:13:40,119 --> 00:13:42,021
And Strawberry Éclairs.

212
00:13:42,021 --> 00:13:43,690
This is our morning menu.

213
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,758
Our menu changes throughout the day.

214
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:48,061
Grandpa, do you want to choose a dessert?

215
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:50,029
This one has strawberries.

216
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:51,664
- No?
- Choose whatever you want.

217
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,733
No, you should choose one.

218
00:13:53,733 --> 00:13:56,869
Which does he prefer,
strawberries or blueberries?

219
00:13:56,869 --> 00:13:58,671
- He can just decide that.
- Grandpa,

220
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:01,174
do you want strawberries or blueberries?

221
00:14:01,174 --> 00:14:02,241
Strawberries?

222
00:14:02,241 --> 00:14:04,210
I'll have what you want.

223
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:06,746
[Going With Granddaughters' Pick]
We'll have Strawberry Éclair,

224
00:14:06,746 --> 00:14:08,281
Green Barley Field Tart, and...

225
00:14:08,281 --> 00:14:10,416
- Green Barley...
- He seems unsure about this one.

226
00:14:10,416 --> 00:14:13,186
[While Seon Ho Takes The Order]

227
00:14:13,953 --> 00:14:16,155
[The Manager Gives A Heads-Up]
We got customers.

228
00:14:16,155 --> 00:14:18,624
They've ordered the Strawberry Éclair
and a few other things.

229
00:14:18,624 --> 00:14:19,559
- Is it doable?
- Yes.

230
00:14:19,559 --> 00:14:21,287
- It's doable.
- Are you sure?

231
00:14:22,762 --> 00:14:25,698
[The Smell Of Bread Fills The Bakery]

232
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:29,902
[What Is This Bread
That Is Slowly Turning Golden?]

233
00:14:32,805 --> 00:14:36,609
[It's Today's Signature Dessert
Bonjour Strawberry Éclair]

234
00:14:38,177 --> 00:14:41,347
[And Its Twin]

235
00:14:41,347 --> 00:14:45,318
[Today's Signature Dessert
Bonjour Blueberry Éclair]

236
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:49,322
[From Strawberries And Blueberries
Locally Grown In Gochang]

237
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:53,426
[Picked Up By Ki Taek And Seon Ho]

238
00:14:53,426 --> 00:14:56,929
[Extra Fresh Strawberries]

239
00:14:56,929 --> 00:14:58,798
[Big As Marbles]

240
00:14:59,532 --> 00:15:02,735
[Very Berry Round Blueberries]

241
00:15:06,339 --> 00:15:09,809
- Strawberry Éclair.
- Strawberry Éclair.

242
00:15:09,809 --> 00:15:12,245
It's beyond compare!

243
00:15:13,546 --> 00:15:15,415
[Today's Dose Of Joy Will Be Provided]

244
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:19,218
[By Our Éclair Friends]

245
00:15:27,527 --> 00:15:30,997
[Cut Off The Top Third Of The Éclair]

246
00:15:48,347 --> 00:15:52,251
[Scoop Out The Inside With Scissors
To Fill It With Cream]

247
00:15:55,588 --> 00:15:57,657
[Helping By Watching]

248
00:16:00,726 --> 00:16:05,097
[Pipe The Vanilla Cream In Two Lines]

249
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:14,140
[The Heat From Your Hands
Can Change The Temperature Of The Cream]

250
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:19,178
[So You Must Be Steady But Quick]

251
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:25,384
[Fill The Remaining 10% With Strawberry Coulis]

252
00:16:31,357 --> 00:16:36,329
[Éclair Means Lightning In French]

253
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:41,501
[It Is Said That They Are So Tasty]

254
00:16:41,501 --> 00:16:44,437
[They Are Eaten In A Flash]

255
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:52,245
[Place Glazed Strawberries
At Each End And In The Middle]

256
00:16:58,651 --> 00:17:02,121
[Fingers Moving As Fast As Lightning]

257
00:17:10,096 --> 00:17:13,633
[Various Textures Are Layered Together]

258
00:17:14,667 --> 00:17:17,603
[Imagine The Richness Of The Flavor]

259
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:21,173
[With All That Packed Into One Single Bite]

260
00:17:25,845 --> 00:17:29,649
[Pipe The Strawberry Cream
In Teardrop Shapes]

261
00:17:46,299 --> 00:17:48,467
Do you want to try adding the hazelnuts?

262
00:17:48,467 --> 00:17:50,770
- Okay.
- Should I leave it to you?

263
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:52,271
[On Second Thought]
But I don't really know...

264
00:17:52,271 --> 00:17:54,106
Do I just put one at a time like this?

265
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:57,009
Move them to the side as you go.

266
00:17:57,009 --> 00:17:58,678
- To make it easier?
- That's right.

267
00:17:58,678 --> 00:17:59,712
[Finished With 3 Roasted Hazelnuts]

268
00:17:59,712 --> 00:18:01,213
[Sigh Of Relief]
It's easier that way now.

269
00:18:01,213 --> 00:18:03,115
Thank you.

270
00:18:03,115 --> 00:18:04,116
- Is it okay?
- Yes.

271
00:18:04,116 --> 00:18:08,120
[Sous Chef Ki Taek Has The Honor
Of Adding The Final Touch]

272
00:18:16,495 --> 00:18:18,998
[Silent Approval]

273
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:45,191
We must be the first customers of the day.

274
00:18:45,191 --> 00:18:46,926
- Yes.
- It seems like it.

275
00:18:46,926 --> 00:18:50,463
Grandpa, you know the letter you sent us

276
00:18:50,463 --> 00:18:52,798
wishing us good fortune for the spring?

277
00:18:52,798 --> 00:18:56,802
I asked my husband to laminate it
so we can hang it on our door.

278
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:58,571
- No.
- He says no.

279
00:18:58,571 --> 00:19:03,142
You need to bring it to someone
who can carve it into wood.

280
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,410
Bring them the letter?

281
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:07,079
- You need to get it engraved.
- That's how you do it.

282
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:09,882
- That's what he means.
- My handwriting isn't special,

283
00:19:09,882 --> 00:19:11,751
- but it will look great engraved.
- Then you can...

284
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:13,285
You can get a little wooden tablet.

285
00:19:13,285 --> 00:19:14,920
- To hang up.
- To hang up.

286
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:16,822
I'd better look for a place.

287
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:18,557
I'll get it engraved and hang that up.

288
00:19:18,557 --> 00:19:20,292
- The children were so surprised.
- Yes.

289
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,427
We showed it to them.

290
00:19:21,427 --> 00:19:23,396
- They asked-
- They were impressed by your handwriting.

291
00:19:23,396 --> 00:19:26,999
They asked how you still knew
all the Chinese characters.

292
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,702
When I was younger,

293
00:19:29,702 --> 00:19:31,871
I studied a little in the seodang.

294
00:19:31,871 --> 00:19:33,039
- Seodang!
- Seodang.

295
00:19:33,039 --> 00:19:35,808
In the olden days,
there were many seodang.

296
00:19:35,808 --> 00:19:36,776
They were all over?

297
00:19:36,776 --> 00:19:39,912
- At the seodang...
- Seodang is so old-timey.

298
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:42,214
- I studied for about two years.
- Orangeade?

299
00:19:42,214 --> 00:19:44,517
- Here you go.
- That's how I learned.

300
00:19:44,517 --> 00:19:46,085
- This is the latte.
- When you were younger?

301
00:19:46,085 --> 00:19:47,186
Yes.

302
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:50,556
- I practiced by writing on newspapers.
- Newspapers?

303
00:19:50,556 --> 00:19:52,058
Yes, that's how I practiced.

304
00:19:52,058 --> 00:19:54,593
Everyone suggested

305
00:19:54,593 --> 00:19:57,763
- I enter a contest.
- Learn about them?

306
00:19:57,763 --> 00:19:58,864
They had contests like that?

307
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,033
Why didn't you do it?

308
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:04,970
- I bet you would have done well.
- I just did it for one reason.

309
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:08,441
I worked at a factory,
and during my break times,

310
00:20:08,441 --> 00:20:12,111
it was a nice way to spend my time.

311
00:20:12,111 --> 00:20:13,871
- That was enough for you?
- I was satisfied.

312
00:20:14,313 --> 00:20:15,715
Try the coffee, Grandpa.

313
00:20:15,715 --> 00:20:18,184
How does it taste?

314
00:20:18,184 --> 00:20:20,252
- Do you like it?
- How is it?

315
00:20:20,252 --> 00:20:22,221
[First Time Trying A Non-Instant Vanilla Latte]

316
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,156
[What Is The Verdict?]

317
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:26,325
- What was it? Vanilla latte?
- Vanilla latte.

318
00:20:26,325 --> 00:20:27,526
- Let us-
- For writing,

319
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:29,729
ink made from pine soot.

320
00:20:31,864 --> 00:20:33,799
[Forget The Coffee]
The containers were this big.

321
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:36,102
[He's Enjoying Chatting With Them]
That's what you used?

322
00:20:36,102 --> 00:20:40,372
- I think I got through 122 containers.
- He used 100 containers?

323
00:20:40,372 --> 00:20:42,875
- Really?
- Yes.

324
00:20:42,875 --> 00:20:45,478
That's how it was back then.

325
00:20:45,478 --> 00:20:46,979
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

326
00:20:46,979 --> 00:20:48,781
- Here is your Crème Brûlée.
- Okay.

327
00:20:48,781 --> 00:20:51,584
- This explains the best way to enjoy it.
- Okay.

328
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:55,087
Use your spoon to crack the top,

329
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:56,956
- Got it.
- Then mix it in before you eat it.

330
00:20:56,956 --> 00:20:58,190
It's a French dessert, right?

331
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,725
- Yes, you're right.
- I see.

332
00:20:59,725 --> 00:21:04,396
Grandpa, this is a French dessert.

333
00:21:04,396 --> 00:21:05,364
- What?
- What you do is,

334
00:21:05,364 --> 00:21:08,467
- you crack the top with your spoon.
- Crack it to eat it.

335
00:21:09,068 --> 00:21:10,569
Tap it like this.

336
00:21:10,569 --> 00:21:13,639
- That's how you eat it?
- You crack it like this.

337
00:21:13,639 --> 00:21:14,907
That's it.

338
00:21:16,542 --> 00:21:18,611
Then you scoop up a bite.

339
00:21:18,611 --> 00:21:20,553
You should try it.

340
00:21:21,814 --> 00:21:23,245
Does it taste good?

341
00:21:24,683 --> 00:21:27,253
Should we take a photo together?

342
00:21:27,253 --> 00:21:28,888
- Look over here.
- What for?

343
00:21:28,888 --> 00:21:31,123
- For a photo.
- Let's take a selfie.

344
00:21:31,123 --> 00:21:32,458
One, two, three.

345
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:35,060
- My face looks too big.
- That's okay.

346
00:21:35,060 --> 00:21:36,462
I'm not okay with it.

347
00:21:36,462 --> 00:21:38,597
How is it? Do you like it?

348
00:21:38,597 --> 00:21:39,832
We haven't tried it yet.

349
00:21:39,832 --> 00:21:41,767
You still haven't tried it?

350
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:42,768
There you go.

351
00:21:42,768 --> 00:21:44,336
[1 Strawberry Éclair, 1 Crème Brûlée,
1 Green Barley Field Tart]

352
00:21:44,336 --> 00:21:45,905
- It's so tasty.
- You like it?

353
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:47,406
Yes, it's really delicious.

354
00:21:47,406 --> 00:21:49,008
Here you go.

355
00:21:50,242 --> 00:21:53,245
- It's so pretty.
- Right?

356
00:21:54,914 --> 00:21:56,382
Is this all handmade?

357
00:21:56,382 --> 00:21:58,988
It's all freshly baked here.

358
00:21:59,748 --> 00:22:03,556
[Chef Cha Is Now Prepping
For The Afternoon Menu]

359
00:22:05,524 --> 00:22:07,026
What's this?

360
00:22:07,026 --> 00:22:09,995
It looks like hazelnuts.

361
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:12,565
[She Guessed Right]
Hazelnuts?

362
00:22:12,565 --> 00:22:14,433
Try a bite of this, Grandpa.

363
00:22:14,433 --> 00:22:16,293
Use your hands if it's easier.

364
00:22:24,944 --> 00:22:26,873
Does it taste good, Grandpa?

365
00:22:31,483 --> 00:22:33,712
- Do you need napkins?
- Yes, please.

366
00:22:49,301 --> 00:22:50,641
He needs some.

367
00:22:51,170 --> 00:22:52,840
Here you go.

368
00:22:54,473 --> 00:22:57,376
These are all French desserts.

369
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:58,844
They're French.

370
00:22:58,844 --> 00:23:00,400
Take a look.

371
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,148
- I want to try this one.
- Shall we cut it?

372
00:23:03,148 --> 00:23:04,149
- I want to try it.
- Okay.

373
00:23:04,149 --> 00:23:05,783
- Cut it.
- Come again.

374
00:23:07,286 --> 00:23:09,355
Why does it say "065 Street"?

375
00:23:09,355 --> 00:23:11,991
- Maybe because it's for seniors over 65.
- Oh, right.

376
00:23:11,991 --> 00:23:13,827
Take a seat over here.

377
00:23:15,053 --> 00:23:16,629
Eat as much as you like, Grandpa.

378
00:23:16,629 --> 00:23:18,530
[2 Whole Èclairs]

379
00:23:18,931 --> 00:23:22,902
It's odd seeing him eating these desserts.

380
00:23:22,902 --> 00:23:26,086
You'd expect seniors not to like these.

381
00:23:26,772 --> 00:23:29,074
- He seems to be enjoying it.
- Yes, it's a relief.

382
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,876
- Do you like it, Grandpa?
- What?

383
00:23:30,876 --> 00:23:33,266
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

384
00:23:34,213 --> 00:23:35,614
Is it to your liking?

385
00:23:35,614 --> 00:23:37,116
- Yes.
- It's so good that we got one more.

386
00:23:37,116 --> 00:23:38,702
Did you?

387
00:23:39,285 --> 00:23:42,021
When we go later,

388
00:23:42,021 --> 00:23:44,690
do you want to buy
a loaf of bread to take home?

389
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:47,293
I want to buy these instead.

390
00:23:47,293 --> 00:23:50,262
- For your grandma.
- I don't think you can take these to go.

391
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:52,197
- You want to take them?
- They're so tasty.

392
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:54,967
- He wants to give them to Grandma.
- Only some desserts can be packaged.

393
00:23:54,967 --> 00:23:55,868
What about these?

394
00:23:55,868 --> 00:23:57,870
- Those can't be packaged.
- I thought so.

395
00:23:57,870 --> 00:23:59,171
We can't take these home.

396
00:23:59,171 --> 00:24:01,507
- You can only eat these here.
- That's right.

397
00:24:01,507 --> 00:24:04,410
[The Creator Is Growing Conflicted]
Those... That's right.

398
00:24:04,410 --> 00:24:07,246
He wants to give them to Grandma.

399
00:24:07,246 --> 00:24:08,347
- I see.
- Yes.

400
00:24:08,347 --> 00:24:10,702
She couldn't come with us today.

401
00:24:11,317 --> 00:24:14,453
- It's not possible, right?
- Can we package leftovers?

402
00:24:14,453 --> 00:24:16,021
Can they take away leftovers?

403
00:24:16,021 --> 00:24:19,024
- Yes, we can package those.
- You can take home leftovers.

404
00:24:19,024 --> 00:24:20,426
Chef Cha.

405
00:24:20,426 --> 00:24:23,562
He wants to take them home for his wife.

406
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:26,665
- Can't we make an exception?
- Let's do this.

407
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:28,667
If they order more to eat here,

408
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:30,569
- we can wrap those up as leftovers.
- Good idea.

409
00:24:30,569 --> 00:24:31,902
Okay.

410
00:24:32,571 --> 00:24:34,340
[Having An Open Discussion]
If they order more to eat here,

411
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:36,241
- we can wrap those up as leftovers.
- Good idea.

412
00:24:36,241 --> 00:24:37,910
Okay.

413
00:24:37,910 --> 00:24:38,811
[It's Off The Record]
Hello.

414
00:24:38,811 --> 00:24:40,346
They just gave us a clever tip.

415
00:24:40,346 --> 00:24:41,513
[We Didn't Say Anything]

416
00:24:41,513 --> 00:24:45,651
Grandmas wouldn't know what to eat
since they're not familiar with it.

417
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:46,785
- Yes.
- I know.

418
00:24:46,785 --> 00:24:48,253
They're new to us as well.

419
00:24:48,253 --> 00:24:50,089
I've never tried this before.

420
00:24:50,089 --> 00:24:51,390
It's good, right?

421
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:53,309
[Answers With A Smile]

422
00:24:54,461 --> 00:24:56,929
Can we take the bread rolls to go?

423
00:24:56,929 --> 00:24:58,530
Yes, you can take them to go.

424
00:24:58,530 --> 00:25:00,643
I'll add bread rolls to your order.

425
00:25:03,736 --> 00:25:05,237
Here's your receipt.

426
00:25:05,237 --> 00:25:08,073
- I also put in some jam.
- Thank you.

427
00:25:08,574 --> 00:25:09,475
Hello.

428
00:25:09,475 --> 00:25:13,545
- Thank you so much.
- These éclairs fall apart really easily.

429
00:25:13,545 --> 00:25:16,115
- We'll treat them preciously.
- Yes, be careful.

430
00:25:16,115 --> 00:25:17,649
- We'll enjoy them with our grandma.
- Okay.

431
00:25:17,649 --> 00:25:18,717
- I hope you enjoy it.
- Thank you.

432
00:25:18,717 --> 00:25:20,452
- Thank you.
- They wrapped it up for us.

433
00:25:20,452 --> 00:25:22,425
I'll carry it.

434
00:25:23,622 --> 00:25:25,724
- Should we sit here for the photo?
- Yes.

435
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:27,059
[At The Young Age Of 50]

436
00:25:27,059 --> 00:25:29,862
[This Gentleman Became A Grandfather]
This place is called Bonjour Bakery.

437
00:25:29,862 --> 00:25:32,765
[Just 43 Years Later]
How did you find out about us?

438
00:25:32,765 --> 00:25:34,333
- We live in Gochang.
- This is our hometown.

439
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:36,068
[His Granddaughters Are Fully Grown]
Our kids go to school here.

440
00:25:36,068 --> 00:25:39,104
[With Children On Their Own]
And grandpa lives near here.

441
00:25:39,104 --> 00:25:42,441
We lived together until elementary school.

442
00:25:42,441 --> 00:25:45,310
We're married and have our own lives now.

443
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,312
He always took good care of us
since we were little.

444
00:25:47,312 --> 00:25:49,448
He really doted on us

445
00:25:49,448 --> 00:25:51,884
and always brought us tasty treats.

446
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:54,753
We lived together until elementary school,

447
00:25:54,753 --> 00:25:58,857
but then we moved
about an hour away into the city.

448
00:25:58,857 --> 00:26:02,795
But every weekend,
he'd travel all that way

449
00:26:02,795 --> 00:26:05,230
to bring us sweet and sour pork,
and that memory has stayed with us.

450
00:26:05,230 --> 00:26:07,666
We even talked about it earlier.

451
00:26:07,666 --> 00:26:11,003
Our kids are now
the age we were back then.

452
00:26:11,003 --> 00:26:13,705
So, he really loves it
when we bring them to visit.

453
00:26:13,705 --> 00:26:18,877
[He's Still Living In Those Golden Days]

454
00:26:21,947 --> 00:26:26,752
[May The Start Of Spring
Bring You Great Joy And Good Fortune]

455
00:26:26,752 --> 00:26:28,153
[Bonjour Bakery]

456
00:26:44,336 --> 00:26:45,637
Is this the entrance?

457
00:26:45,637 --> 00:26:47,539
[Laughing]

458
00:26:47,539 --> 00:26:49,241
Those flowers are pretty.

459
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:52,211
Look at the pretty flower.

460
00:26:52,211 --> 00:26:53,378
It's cold.

461
00:26:53,378 --> 00:26:54,980
Should we go inside?

462
00:26:54,980 --> 00:26:57,816
Leave that here before we head in.

463
00:26:57,816 --> 00:26:59,084
Put it on the side.

464
00:26:59,084 --> 00:27:00,919
[The Perfect Customers]
Just leave them there.

465
00:27:00,919 --> 00:27:03,589
[For A Slow-Moving Cafe]
Can I just leave it here?

466
00:27:05,090 --> 00:27:06,258
Is this the place?

467
00:27:06,258 --> 00:27:07,726
Yes, let's go in.

468
00:27:07,726 --> 00:27:09,109
Let's go inside.

469
00:27:10,963 --> 00:27:13,398
- Hello.
- Hello.

470
00:27:13,832 --> 00:27:15,343
Let's go inside.

471
00:27:16,702 --> 00:27:18,170
- Hello.
- Hello.

472
00:27:18,170 --> 00:27:19,338
Hello.

473
00:27:20,239 --> 00:27:23,311
Come on in. Take a seat over here.

474
00:27:27,713 --> 00:27:29,414
Please sit here.

475
00:27:29,414 --> 00:27:30,782
Are you a party of five?

476
00:27:30,782 --> 00:27:32,317
- Please go over there.
- Over there.

477
00:27:32,317 --> 00:27:35,326
You'll be more comfortable in there
if there are five of you.

478
00:27:36,388 --> 00:27:38,624
[Bonjour Bakery Has Spacious Parking]
Welcome.

479
00:27:38,624 --> 00:27:40,501
We're so glad to have you.

480
00:27:43,061 --> 00:27:44,997
- Hello.
- Hello.

481
00:27:44,997 --> 00:27:47,862
Take a seat in there.
You came with the group, right?

482
00:27:50,075 --> 00:27:52,204
- Hello, ma'am.
- How do I get past?

483
00:27:52,204 --> 00:27:54,072
- You must be exhausted.
- Yes.

484
00:27:54,072 --> 00:27:59,611
- I've seen your face a lot somewhere.
- Yes.

485
00:27:59,611 --> 00:28:00,679
You're...

486
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:03,478
- My name is Kim Hee Ae.
- I know.

487
00:28:04,149 --> 00:28:05,150
You're...

488
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:08,187
- My name is Kim Hee Ae.
- I know.

489
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:09,488
- You haven't changed.
- Yes.

490
00:28:09,488 --> 00:28:12,057
- Did you see Son and Daughter?
- Yes.

491
00:28:12,057 --> 00:28:13,859
- I played the character Hu Nam.
- I know.

492
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:15,160
[Who?]

493
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:17,930
I recognized you at once.
You haven't changed at all.

494
00:28:17,930 --> 00:28:19,464
- She was a character on TV.
- Hu Nam.

495
00:28:19,464 --> 00:28:21,700
There used to be a TV drama
called Son and Daughter.

496
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:22,668
I don't know it.

497
00:28:22,668 --> 00:28:23,802
I'll be back in a minute.

498
00:28:23,802 --> 00:28:25,303
Okay.

499
00:28:28,941 --> 00:28:30,108
It looks fancy.

500
00:28:30,108 --> 00:28:32,978
It looks more spacious like this.

501
00:28:32,978 --> 00:28:35,614
Isn't Dong Cheon's mom coming?

502
00:28:35,614 --> 00:28:37,716
Isn't Dong Cheon's mom coming?

503
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,085
Should I call her and tell her to come?

504
00:28:40,719 --> 00:28:42,287
I'll do it.

505
00:28:42,287 --> 00:28:46,225
I heard one of you owns this building.

506
00:28:46,225 --> 00:28:47,726
- What?
- This building.

507
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:49,328
- That's her.
- I see.

508
00:28:49,328 --> 00:28:51,129
Hello, ma'am.

509
00:28:51,129 --> 00:28:52,931
[It's Me]

510
00:28:55,434 --> 00:28:57,836
[Her Mind Is On Dong Cheon's Mom]
Use this to wipe your hands.

511
00:28:57,836 --> 00:29:01,807
These are French desserts.

512
00:29:01,807 --> 00:29:04,042
This was made with Gochang strawberries.

513
00:29:04,042 --> 00:29:06,478
All the ingredients are locally grown.

514
00:29:06,478 --> 00:29:08,733
- Have a look at the menu.
- Okay.

515
00:29:10,949 --> 00:29:12,384
Take your time deciding.

516
00:29:12,384 --> 00:29:13,785
[Host Of The Group]
Choose what you want to eat.

517
00:29:13,785 --> 00:29:15,287
Did you perm your hair?

518
00:29:15,287 --> 00:29:16,622
- What?
- Did you not get a perm?

519
00:29:16,622 --> 00:29:18,390
I'm not sure. I don't think so.

520
00:29:18,390 --> 00:29:20,058
Call Dong Bang's mom.

521
00:29:20,058 --> 00:29:21,960
Don't put your phone away.

522
00:29:23,161 --> 00:29:25,397
And ask her what? If she's cooking?

523
00:29:25,397 --> 00:29:28,133
- Call Dong Bang's mom.
- Tell her to come here.

524
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:29,101
She was here earlier.

525
00:29:29,101 --> 00:29:30,941
No, she didn't come with us.

526
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:34,239
- Look at the airplane.
- What?

527
00:29:34,239 --> 00:29:35,774
An airplane.

528
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:37,276
They're filming.

529
00:29:37,276 --> 00:29:40,279
They're filming from there.

530
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:41,713
It goes back and forth.

531
00:29:41,713 --> 00:29:43,782
It goes around in circles.

532
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:45,183
Here she comes.

533
00:29:45,183 --> 00:29:46,730
Over here!

534
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,422
Take a seat here.

535
00:29:50,422 --> 00:29:51,923
[Park Bong Ja Aka Dong Cheon's Mom]

536
00:29:52,658 --> 00:29:55,360
[Returning Customer]

537
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:56,328
Did you order yet?

538
00:29:56,328 --> 00:29:58,263
- Not yet.
- What do we order?

539
00:29:58,263 --> 00:29:59,631
We need to choose from the menu.

540
00:29:59,631 --> 00:30:01,366
[The Youngest Gets Things Going]
We don't know what's what.

541
00:30:01,366 --> 00:30:03,803
What bread should we eat?

542
00:30:05,771 --> 00:30:08,206
[So Many New Items]
Strawberries.

543
00:30:08,206 --> 00:30:09,775
How do you know what's good?

544
00:30:09,775 --> 00:30:12,010
I don't. I've never tried these.

545
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:13,679
[Nice Timing]
Hello.

546
00:30:13,679 --> 00:30:16,415
- Use these to wipe your hands.
- All right.

547
00:30:16,415 --> 00:30:18,317
[Happy To Follow]
We'll do that.

548
00:30:18,317 --> 00:30:19,318
- I'll use these.
- Okay.

549
00:30:19,318 --> 00:30:21,353
I'll bring you one more in a moment.

550
00:30:21,353 --> 00:30:23,555
Would you like to order?

551
00:30:23,555 --> 00:30:25,123
What should we order?

552
00:30:25,123 --> 00:30:26,525
What's good here?

553
00:30:26,525 --> 00:30:28,126
If you look here,

554
00:30:28,126 --> 00:30:29,761
[Today's Special Editions]
these are only available today.

555
00:30:29,761 --> 00:30:30,996
It's called Blueberry Éclair,

556
00:30:30,996 --> 00:30:33,031
and it's a French dessert.

557
00:30:33,031 --> 00:30:35,000
It's made personally by Cha Seung Won.

558
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:37,536
I also recommend the Strawberry Éclair.

559
00:30:37,536 --> 00:30:39,604
[Emphasizing Their Freshness]
We picked up the strawberries today.

560
00:30:39,604 --> 00:30:40,972
Give us whatever is tastiest.

561
00:30:40,972 --> 00:30:44,209
Okay, one Strawberry Éclair.

562
00:30:44,209 --> 00:30:46,211
How about Green Barley Field Tart?

563
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:48,280
Green barley is a local specialty.

564
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:51,783
We used it to make cream and cake.

565
00:30:51,783 --> 00:30:53,785
Just get us something good.

566
00:30:53,785 --> 00:30:55,654
Something good.
One Green Barley Tart coming up.

567
00:30:55,654 --> 00:30:57,155
Yes, give us something delicious.

568
00:30:57,155 --> 00:30:58,990
They must have taken
the green barley from the fields.

569
00:30:58,990 --> 00:31:00,892
Yes, we used the local green barley.

570
00:31:00,892 --> 00:31:02,227
How about Sweet Potato Cake?

571
00:31:02,227 --> 00:31:03,462
[Copy And Repeat]
Sweet Potato Cake?

572
00:31:03,462 --> 00:31:05,130
- Is that okay?
- Yes.

573
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:07,199
[Anything Tasty Is Fine]
One Sweet Potato Cake.

574
00:31:07,199 --> 00:31:09,334
If we order 3 desserts
and share them among 6 people...

575
00:31:09,334 --> 00:31:10,469
That's a good amount.

576
00:31:10,469 --> 00:31:12,671
I'll bring your order in a flash.

577
00:31:12,671 --> 00:31:16,041
- It's worth paying to try something new.
- It's luxury bread.

578
00:31:16,041 --> 00:31:18,710
Yes, we could die any day,
so let's splurge a little.

579
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:20,912
"We could die any day."

580
00:31:20,912 --> 00:31:23,782
A woman should eat
expensive food once in her life.

581
00:31:25,550 --> 00:31:27,486
It's a nice world we're living in.

582
00:31:27,486 --> 00:31:29,354
I've been around long enough to see this.

583
00:31:29,354 --> 00:31:30,389
You're right.

584
00:31:30,389 --> 00:31:32,190
Good thing we stayed alive.

585
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:33,625
Places like this didn't exist.

586
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:35,527
What's the point of living a long life?

587
00:31:35,527 --> 00:31:38,530
You need to get better
and enjoy a long, healthy life.

588
00:31:38,530 --> 00:31:41,299
It's too late for me to get better.

589
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:44,102
I just hope the pain doesn't get worse.

590
00:31:44,503 --> 00:31:46,304
The desserts for Table Five are ready.

591
00:31:46,304 --> 00:31:48,273
All right. Thank you.

592
00:31:48,273 --> 00:31:50,242
No problem.

593
00:31:50,242 --> 00:31:51,376
There are six of you?

594
00:31:51,376 --> 00:31:54,646
This is a description of the desserts.

595
00:31:54,646 --> 00:31:57,682
- You can keep them as a fun souvenir.
- Is that right?

596
00:31:57,682 --> 00:31:59,885
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

597
00:31:59,885 --> 00:32:01,887
- I brought the Americano first.
- Okay.

598
00:32:01,887 --> 00:32:02,921
That's for me.

599
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,222
Thank you.

600
00:32:05,657 --> 00:32:07,225
It's hot. Be careful.

601
00:32:07,793 --> 00:32:10,028
- He's so considerate.
- He is.

602
00:32:10,028 --> 00:32:11,296
Would you like us to cut it for you?

603
00:32:11,296 --> 00:32:13,165
- Yes, please.
- Yes, cut it.

604
00:32:13,165 --> 00:32:16,134
[Elegant Hee Ae's Eyes Dart Back And Forth]

605
00:32:17,869 --> 00:32:20,205
I'm not good at this.

606
00:32:20,205 --> 00:32:23,208
- That's okay.
- I don't want to ruin the cake.

607
00:32:23,208 --> 00:32:24,476
It doesn't have to be neat.

608
00:32:24,476 --> 00:32:26,178
- All right.
- It's going in our stomachs.

609
00:32:26,178 --> 00:32:27,746
There are six of you...

610
00:32:27,746 --> 00:32:28,947
Yes, cut it like that.

611
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:30,449
I'll divide it into six equal pieces.

612
00:32:30,449 --> 00:32:32,049
[I, Kim Hee Ae, Will Divide This For You]

613
00:32:33,018 --> 00:32:35,420
[One Piece]

614
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:38,056
[Two Pieces]

615
00:32:38,056 --> 00:32:40,192
[Three Pieces]

616
00:32:40,192 --> 00:32:42,227
[Four Pieces]

617
00:32:42,227 --> 00:32:44,830
[Five Pieces]

618
00:32:46,097 --> 00:32:48,834
[And Finally, Six Pieces!]

619
00:32:48,834 --> 00:32:50,402
No need to be nervous.

620
00:32:50,402 --> 00:32:51,783
Right.

621
00:32:53,371 --> 00:32:54,773
Do you like sweet potatoes?

622
00:32:54,773 --> 00:32:56,975
Yes, it's very sweet.

623
00:32:57,909 --> 00:33:00,779
You three can share this plate.

624
00:33:00,779 --> 00:33:02,581
Thank you.

625
00:33:02,581 --> 00:33:05,417
The strawberries were picked this morning.

626
00:33:07,419 --> 00:33:09,654
That's a knife.

627
00:33:09,654 --> 00:33:11,690
[Whatever]

628
00:33:12,457 --> 00:33:13,705
Let's try it.

629
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:16,437
Eat up.

630
00:33:23,702 --> 00:33:24,970
It's delicious.

631
00:33:24,970 --> 00:33:26,037
- You like it?
- Yes.

632
00:33:26,037 --> 00:33:28,206
It's made from local sweet potatoes.

633
00:33:28,206 --> 00:33:29,692
Yes, it's great.

634
00:33:38,250 --> 00:33:39,865
It's so tasty.

635
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:44,122
Have a taste. It's good.

636
00:33:44,122 --> 00:33:45,857
[The Queen Introvert]
Go on.

637
00:33:45,857 --> 00:33:47,592
Try some.

638
00:33:48,093 --> 00:33:49,876
Pick it up with a fork.

639
00:33:50,562 --> 00:33:51,696
[Incomprehensible
Did you go to Burger Park?

640
00:33:51,696 --> 00:33:53,298
- What was that?
- Never mind.

641
00:33:53,298 --> 00:33:55,160
I was just urging her to eat.

642
00:33:55,867 --> 00:33:57,024
Please dig in.

643
00:33:57,636 --> 00:33:59,804
Take this piece instead.

644
00:33:59,804 --> 00:34:01,072
This one...

645
00:34:02,140 --> 00:34:04,042
[She Feels Shy In Front Of Hee Ae]
This is for you three to share.

646
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:07,145
[But Bravely Takes A Bite]
Try that.

647
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,188
Take a piece.

648
00:34:18,957 --> 00:34:21,192
[Silently Takes Another Bite]

649
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:31,102
This is really hard to make.

650
00:34:31,102 --> 00:34:34,372
The green barley gives it this color.

651
00:34:34,372 --> 00:34:37,857
It also contains citron,
so you can taste a mixture of flavors.

652
00:34:46,184 --> 00:34:47,385
Try that.

653
00:34:47,385 --> 00:34:50,555
[Recommends Anything That Tastes Good
Without Hesitation]

654
00:34:51,456 --> 00:34:52,926
I tried it already.

655
00:34:52,926 --> 00:34:55,194
[I Feel Drawn To This Éclair]

656
00:35:00,098 --> 00:35:03,401
This is the coffee and drinks menu.

657
00:35:03,401 --> 00:35:05,837
And back here is the dessert menu.

658
00:35:06,638 --> 00:35:08,106
How is it? Do you like it?

659
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:09,946
- Does it taste good?
- Tell me what you think.

660
00:35:10,508 --> 00:35:11,509
- Is it good?
- Yes.

661
00:35:11,509 --> 00:35:13,411
- You should say, "It's delicious."
- So cute.

662
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:17,449
- Haven't you taken their order yet?
- Table Three ordered an éclair.

663
00:35:17,449 --> 00:35:19,384
Table Three ordered one more éclair.

664
00:35:19,384 --> 00:35:20,785
One more éclair for Table Three.

665
00:35:20,785 --> 00:35:22,354
- I already checked it off.
- Then I just...

666
00:35:22,354 --> 00:35:24,422
- You see those two?
- Oh, I see.

667
00:35:24,422 --> 00:35:25,323
- Did you ring it up?
- Yes.

668
00:35:25,323 --> 00:35:27,025
- One éclair.
- Make sure to press the order button.

669
00:35:27,025 --> 00:35:28,526
I need to press the order button?

670
00:35:28,526 --> 00:35:29,961
Let me take a look.

671
00:35:29,961 --> 00:35:31,296
You ring it up,

672
00:35:31,296 --> 00:35:35,195
then press the order button
to print the receipt.

673
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:45,243
[Vanilla Latte Made By Seon Ho]

674
00:35:51,549 --> 00:35:53,585
[Nice And Refreshing]

675
00:35:57,889 --> 00:36:00,725
[We Can't Resist This Latte]

676
00:36:04,262 --> 00:36:06,164
I think this is the place.

677
00:36:06,164 --> 00:36:08,099
- Bonjour Bakery.
- Yes.

678
00:36:11,436 --> 00:36:14,272
- Bakery...
- Why is this flipped over?

679
00:36:17,142 --> 00:36:19,044
- Hello.
- Hello.

680
00:36:19,044 --> 00:36:20,378
- Hello.
- Hello.

681
00:36:20,378 --> 00:36:22,213
- Hello.
- Welcome.

682
00:36:24,883 --> 00:36:27,218
♪ Bonjour Bakery ♪

683
00:36:27,952 --> 00:36:33,825
[A Young Lady Has Brought
Her Dad And His Friends]

684
00:36:33,825 --> 00:36:35,060
[Spots The Magnifying Glass]
What's this?

685
00:36:35,060 --> 00:36:36,995
It's for elderly people to see better.

686
00:36:36,995 --> 00:36:38,463
To see what?

687
00:36:38,463 --> 00:36:39,731
When they bring the menu and stuff,

688
00:36:39,731 --> 00:36:41,032
you can use it to take a closer look.

689
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:43,735
- For older seniors?
- That's right.

690
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:45,103
[Instantly Puts It Down]

691
00:36:45,103 --> 00:36:46,404
You don't need it, Dad?

692
00:36:47,072 --> 00:36:47,972
That's right.

693
00:36:47,972 --> 00:36:50,408
We're not that old.

694
00:36:50,408 --> 00:36:52,410
[The Three Friends Insist They're Not That Old]

695
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,578
- Can I have a moment?
- Sure.

696
00:36:53,578 --> 00:36:55,647
- Here is the menu.
- Thank you.

697
00:36:55,647 --> 00:36:57,549
- Use these wet towels to wipe your hands.
- Okay.

698
00:36:57,549 --> 00:36:59,531
Have a look and take your time deciding.

699
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:04,589
The towel is so warm.

700
00:37:04,589 --> 00:37:07,625
It feels nice and toasty.

701
00:37:08,426 --> 00:37:11,529
- You've gifted us a special experience.
- Exactly.

702
00:37:11,529 --> 00:37:15,100
We get to check out a place like this
thanks to your daughter.

703
00:37:15,100 --> 00:37:16,501
- It's nice here, isn't it?
- Yes.

704
00:37:16,501 --> 00:37:18,103
[Enjoying A New Experience]
And the weather's so nice today.

705
00:37:18,103 --> 00:37:22,006
Eat to your heart's content.
I get to play the dutiful daughter today.

706
00:37:22,741 --> 00:37:24,809
- How do we pay?
- What?

707
00:37:24,809 --> 00:37:26,411
- Where do we pay?
- I don't know.

708
00:37:26,411 --> 00:37:28,246
I heard Yong Ho is buying.

709
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:29,481
Yes, it's my treat.

710
00:37:29,481 --> 00:37:30,515
- Right?
- Yes.

711
00:37:30,515 --> 00:37:32,217
[My Son Told Me To Pay]
I'm treating you.

712
00:37:32,217 --> 00:37:33,818
- Are you really?
- Yes.

713
00:37:33,818 --> 00:37:37,655
Her son told her to treat
the old ladies at the Village Hall.

714
00:37:37,655 --> 00:37:40,525
You're going to buy all of this?

715
00:37:40,525 --> 00:37:42,894
- Yes.
- Her son told her to.

716
00:37:42,894 --> 00:37:44,462
- Don't do that.
- My son told me

717
00:37:44,462 --> 00:37:47,365
to treat the old ladies
at the Village Hall.

718
00:37:47,365 --> 00:37:49,167
It's such a treat.

719
00:37:49,167 --> 00:37:50,068
Thank you.

720
00:37:50,068 --> 00:37:51,469
- What?
- Thanks a lot.

721
00:37:51,469 --> 00:37:53,138
- Forget that.
- Just eat.

722
00:37:53,138 --> 00:37:54,706
[The Village Hall Ladies]
Have the rest of that.

723
00:37:54,706 --> 00:37:57,609
[Keep Urging Each Other To Eat]
Finish off the rest of the drink.

724
00:37:57,609 --> 00:38:00,245
- Finish it all.
- Have it.

725
00:38:00,245 --> 00:38:01,379
Let me have some.

726
00:38:01,379 --> 00:38:03,481
- Eat it all.
- It's all gone.

727
00:38:14,159 --> 00:38:17,362
[They Leave The Place Spotless]

728
00:38:23,334 --> 00:38:24,502
[Glancing Over]

729
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:26,938
Those ladies are all in good shape.

730
00:38:27,605 --> 00:38:29,707
They seem fit and healthy.

731
00:38:29,707 --> 00:38:31,376
- Yes.
- They do.

732
00:38:32,377 --> 00:38:34,879
It's warmer here than I expected.

733
00:38:34,879 --> 00:38:36,981
I heard it's going up to 10 degrees.

734
00:38:36,981 --> 00:38:41,152
[It's Hard To Take Your Eyes Off Them]

735
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:42,487
People who live in the countryside-

736
00:38:42,487 --> 00:38:44,255
Ma'am, do you live around here?

737
00:38:44,255 --> 00:38:45,423
Do you live in the area?

738
00:38:45,423 --> 00:38:47,225
- Do you live around here?
- Speak louder.

739
00:38:47,225 --> 00:38:48,993
Yes, I do.

740
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:50,695
I spend time at the Village Hall up here.

741
00:38:50,695 --> 00:38:52,878
- Oh, I see.
- I'm always there.

742
00:38:53,998 --> 00:38:56,067
How old are you, ma'am?

743
00:38:56,067 --> 00:38:57,435
- What?
- How old are you?

744
00:38:57,435 --> 00:38:58,336
Your age.

745
00:38:58,336 --> 00:39:00,338
I've lost track because I'm so old.

746
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:02,774
Have a think.
I think we're about the same age.

747
00:39:03,541 --> 00:39:06,311
- I'm unbelievably old.
- "Unbelievably."

748
00:39:06,311 --> 00:39:07,512
Eighty...

749
00:39:07,512 --> 00:39:08,913
- Eighty...
- I'm 87 years old.

750
00:39:08,913 --> 00:39:10,415
Oh, my.

751
00:39:10,415 --> 00:39:12,383
- You're in great shape.
- Your skin is so fair.

752
00:39:12,383 --> 00:39:16,888
How am I in good shape?
I can barely stand up straight.

753
00:39:16,888 --> 00:39:18,289
- You look healthy.
- Really?

754
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:21,259
- Your face is radiant.
- I can't get around on my own.

755
00:39:21,259 --> 00:39:23,862
But you don't have that many wrinkles.

756
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:25,496
You managed to come all this way.

757
00:39:25,496 --> 00:39:27,365
Get back safely.

758
00:39:29,334 --> 00:39:31,169
[Discussing Which Desserts To Take Home]

759
00:39:34,272 --> 00:39:35,406
They're going all out.

760
00:39:35,406 --> 00:39:38,943
- I need to buy it now that I've tried it.
- All right.

761
00:39:38,943 --> 00:39:40,778
- I'll be back to buy more.
- What was that?

762
00:39:40,778 --> 00:39:42,847
- I live here, so I'll come back.
- We'll be back for more.

763
00:39:42,847 --> 00:39:44,446
That's good.

764
00:39:47,418 --> 00:39:50,154
- Try the jam in here with the bread.
- Okay.

765
00:39:51,122 --> 00:39:53,124
Thank you, ma'am.

766
00:39:53,925 --> 00:39:56,319
Ma'am, here's your change.

767
00:39:56,319 --> 00:39:58,663
Take that along with the receipt.

768
00:39:58,663 --> 00:40:00,932
You're even giving us a bag?

769
00:40:00,932 --> 00:40:02,300
Keep it as a souvenir.

770
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:04,369
Have this jam with the bread.

771
00:40:04,369 --> 00:40:07,346
- Put it on the bread before you eat it.
- Okay.

772
00:40:07,972 --> 00:40:09,474
How much is the jam?

773
00:40:09,474 --> 00:40:12,143
This is a gift from us.

774
00:40:12,143 --> 00:40:13,144
Take the money.

775
00:40:13,144 --> 00:40:14,652
No, it's really okay.

776
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:17,815
- Please come again.
- We will.

777
00:40:17,815 --> 00:40:19,984
Thank you, ma'am.

778
00:40:39,170 --> 00:40:42,373
[Bonjour Bakery]

779
00:40:46,346 --> 00:40:51,551
[Meanwhile Barista Seon Ho]

780
00:40:53,184 --> 00:40:56,421
[Finishes Up Making
An Americano With Golden Crema]

781
00:40:56,421 --> 00:40:59,991
This friend here doesn't turn around

782
00:40:59,991 --> 00:41:02,760
- if someone calls her a grandma.
- That's not it.

783
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:05,730
- She walks away thinking it's not her.
- She's mistaken.

784
00:41:05,730 --> 00:41:06,798
Hear me out.

785
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:09,867
I'm not used to being called a grandma.

786
00:41:09,867 --> 00:41:12,236
I assume they mean someone else.

787
00:41:13,404 --> 00:41:15,406
Here are two more cappuccinos.

788
00:41:16,607 --> 00:41:18,676
- This is for you.
- Thank you.

789
00:41:18,676 --> 00:41:21,946
Here's the Sweet Potato Cake.
Make sure to take the wrapper off.

790
00:41:21,946 --> 00:41:23,781
- This is the Green Barley Brioche.
- Okay.

791
00:41:23,781 --> 00:41:27,518
- Use these knives to cut them.
- Thank you.

792
00:41:27,518 --> 00:41:29,253
I'll bring you two more forks.

793
00:41:29,253 --> 00:41:33,191
- Can we order more after we try it?
- Order as much as you like.

794
00:41:33,191 --> 00:41:35,426
I'll go get the rest.

795
00:41:35,426 --> 00:41:37,328
It's a bit bigger than I thought.

796
00:41:37,328 --> 00:41:39,137
Where do I put this?

797
00:41:40,698 --> 00:41:43,401
[One Large Green Barley Brioche]

798
00:41:44,535 --> 00:41:49,707
[The First Customers To Try
The Bonjour Green Barley Brioche]

799
00:41:50,942 --> 00:41:52,877
[One Big Bite]

800
00:41:56,547 --> 00:41:58,182
This dessert...

801
00:41:58,182 --> 00:42:00,051
It's tasty and not too sweet.

802
00:42:00,051 --> 00:42:03,087
It tastes a bit like matcha
because of the green barley.

803
00:42:03,087 --> 00:42:04,555
It's similar to matcha.

804
00:42:05,423 --> 00:42:07,592
It's very tasty.

805
00:42:08,493 --> 00:42:10,794
- It's good.
- Yes.

806
00:42:12,797 --> 00:42:13,931
[A New Group Is At The Big Table]
Have this, Dad.

807
00:42:13,931 --> 00:42:14,999
Is it good?

808
00:42:14,999 --> 00:42:16,801
- It's grain.
- Yes, I noticed.

809
00:42:16,801 --> 00:42:19,287
- Grain?
- Isn't it an almond?

810
00:42:19,871 --> 00:42:21,039
Aren't they almonds?

811
00:42:22,306 --> 00:42:24,088
I think they're peanuts.

812
00:42:25,276 --> 00:42:27,178
[Another Bite]

813
00:42:27,178 --> 00:42:28,707
It's delicious.

814
00:42:31,682 --> 00:42:34,385
I need to have one more bite.

815
00:42:36,888 --> 00:42:37,789
[Green Barley Field Tart]

816
00:42:37,789 --> 00:42:38,956
I'm good, thanks.

817
00:42:40,191 --> 00:42:43,394
[Full Of Praise]
Everything tastes great.

818
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:45,563
[His Daughters Are Pleased By His Reaction]

819
00:42:47,532 --> 00:42:48,866
Are you okay now, Dad?

820
00:42:48,866 --> 00:42:50,635
Yes.

821
00:42:50,635 --> 00:42:52,203
You don't have any more swelling?

822
00:42:52,203 --> 00:42:54,238
No.

823
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:57,108
- You're a miracle case, Dad.
- You're right.

824
00:42:57,108 --> 00:42:59,410
Everyone says so, right?

825
00:43:03,948 --> 00:43:06,184
You got so lucky,
just like last time your throat hurt.

826
00:43:06,184 --> 00:43:08,953
It's a real miracle.

827
00:43:08,953 --> 00:43:11,622
It's not the kind of thing
most people recover from.

828
00:43:12,123 --> 00:43:14,725
Can you stop going
to the hospital after May?

829
00:43:14,725 --> 00:43:16,494
- No, he needs to keep going.
- I need to go.

830
00:43:16,494 --> 00:43:19,130
- They have to check his progress.
- He needs a follow-up.

831
00:43:19,130 --> 00:43:20,364
[He Needs Post-Chemo Check-Ups]

832
00:43:20,364 --> 00:43:22,767
- At least he's done with chemo now.
- Yes.

833
00:43:28,039 --> 00:43:30,842
I was worried he wouldn't handle chemo.

834
00:43:30,842 --> 00:43:31,976
It was hard on Mom.

835
00:43:31,976 --> 00:43:34,479
Mom could only do one round.
I thought Dad couldn't handle it at all.

836
00:43:34,479 --> 00:43:38,716
- It's unbelievably hard.
- I exercised for four hours a day.

837
00:43:38,716 --> 00:43:40,318
- I got up at 3:30 a.m.
- You were unbelievable.

838
00:43:40,318 --> 00:43:42,420
- And exercised for two hours.
- It was so intense.

839
00:43:43,020 --> 00:43:45,490
- I did that five days a week.
- It's so impressive.

840
00:43:45,490 --> 00:43:48,159
Don't push yourself too hard.

841
00:43:48,159 --> 00:43:50,428
I exercise by walking.

842
00:43:50,428 --> 00:43:51,829
Ten thousand steps.

843
00:43:51,829 --> 00:43:53,464
That's how much I walk.

844
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:56,868
It's been hard on these two.

845
00:43:58,836 --> 00:44:02,073
[He Was Able To Overcome]

846
00:44:02,073 --> 00:44:05,143
[Because His Family Stuck By Him]

847
00:44:05,676 --> 00:44:07,345
Why don't you try out next year?

848
00:44:07,345 --> 00:44:10,348
Try out for the 5km marathon.

849
00:44:13,618 --> 00:44:15,077
- This is nice.
- Yes.

850
00:44:16,020 --> 00:44:20,224
[It's Even More Precious
Because Of All They've Overcome]

851
00:44:35,072 --> 00:44:37,942
[Someone Is Slowly Making Their Way Over]

852
00:44:39,177 --> 00:44:42,180
[He Walks Slowly And Steadily]

853
00:44:46,817 --> 00:44:49,987
[And Takes A Moment To Gaze At The Flowers]

854
00:44:52,657 --> 00:44:55,259
[Customers Heading Out]

855
00:44:55,259 --> 00:44:56,527
Don't overexert yourself.

856
00:44:59,096 --> 00:45:02,466
[They Escort Him]

857
00:45:06,404 --> 00:45:08,873
[Park Heon Gu]

858
00:45:15,246 --> 00:45:17,648
[Park The Cane]

859
00:45:18,649 --> 00:45:19,584
Hello.

860
00:45:19,584 --> 00:45:21,219
- Are you here alone?
- Sorry?

861
00:45:21,219 --> 00:45:22,887
Did you come here alone?

862
00:45:22,887 --> 00:45:24,956
My wife said she couldn't come.

863
00:45:24,956 --> 00:45:26,123
So, it's just you?

864
00:45:26,123 --> 00:45:28,226
- Yes.
- I see.

865
00:45:30,127 --> 00:45:32,730
[The Menu]

866
00:45:36,901 --> 00:45:38,569
- How much...
- Sorry?

867
00:45:38,569 --> 00:45:39,904
How much do I give...

868
00:45:39,904 --> 00:45:41,439
Sorry, I didn't catch that.

869
00:45:41,439 --> 00:45:43,107
How much do I give you?

870
00:45:43,107 --> 00:45:45,409
Can you say that one more time?

871
00:45:48,045 --> 00:45:49,947
[He Brings His Wallet Out]

872
00:45:49,947 --> 00:45:53,117
You can pay later after you've eaten.

873
00:45:53,117 --> 00:45:54,085
Okay.

874
00:45:54,085 --> 00:45:57,888
This is a French dessert café.

875
00:45:57,888 --> 00:46:01,659
You can order a hot tea or a hot coffee.

876
00:46:02,693 --> 00:46:04,695
My daughter said you had rice cake sticks.

877
00:46:04,695 --> 00:46:06,430
- Cash?
- Rice cake sticks.

878
00:46:06,430 --> 00:46:07,698
- Oh, rice cake sticks?
- Yes.

879
00:46:07,698 --> 00:46:10,501
We don't serve Korean-style desserts.

880
00:46:10,501 --> 00:46:15,072
We only serve French desserts.

881
00:46:15,072 --> 00:46:16,841
I was told you had rice cake sticks.

882
00:46:16,841 --> 00:46:18,309
- Sorry?
- Don't you know what that is?

883
00:46:18,309 --> 00:46:19,710
- Rice cake sticks?
- Yes.

884
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:21,545
We don't sell those.

885
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:23,614
Oh, dear.

886
00:46:23,614 --> 00:46:25,549
You can try something new.

887
00:46:25,549 --> 00:46:30,388
We only sell French desserts here.

888
00:46:30,388 --> 00:46:31,922
How much is it?

889
00:46:31,922 --> 00:46:36,494
This one here is made of strawberries
that were picked this morning, so...

890
00:46:36,494 --> 00:46:39,063
[How About An Éclair
Made Of Freshly Picked Strawberries?]

891
00:46:39,063 --> 00:46:40,631
How much is it?

892
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:42,466
It's 8,000 won.

893
00:46:42,466 --> 00:46:44,635
This one's made of green barley.

894
00:46:45,903 --> 00:46:47,571
[A Warm, Soft Brioche]

895
00:46:47,571 --> 00:46:50,608
[Topped With Green Barley Sablé]

896
00:46:52,109 --> 00:46:53,878
How much is this? Is it 5,000 won?

897
00:46:53,878 --> 00:46:55,303
Yes.

898
00:46:58,149 --> 00:47:00,451
[Magnifying Glass]
Use that to take a closer look.

899
00:47:00,451 --> 00:47:03,533
You can read the menu more clearly.

900
00:47:07,058 --> 00:47:08,759
"Gochang."

901
00:47:09,512 --> 00:47:13,764
"A Madeleine made
with Gochang's renowned bokbunja."

902
00:47:13,764 --> 00:47:16,167
This dessert is called a "Madeleine."

903
00:47:16,167 --> 00:47:17,168
Give me one of those.

904
00:47:17,168 --> 00:47:19,603
- Would you like this one?
- Yes, please.

905
00:47:19,603 --> 00:47:22,606
What about drinks?
Would you like warm water?

906
00:47:22,606 --> 00:47:26,210
- What?
- Do you want water or coffee?

907
00:47:26,210 --> 00:47:27,345
I don't drink coffee.

908
00:47:27,345 --> 00:47:29,080
- I'll bring you some water.
- Okay.

909
00:47:29,080 --> 00:47:30,307
All right.

910
00:47:32,917 --> 00:47:35,119
[Waiting To Try A French Dessert
For The First Time]

911
00:47:36,454 --> 00:47:40,491
[There Are 3 Types Of Baked Goods For Sale]

912
00:47:42,059 --> 00:47:44,028
[Bonjour Financier]

913
00:47:45,429 --> 00:47:47,565
[Bonjour Citron Madeleine]

914
00:47:48,833 --> 00:47:51,869
[In Addition To These From The Original Lineup]

915
00:47:53,170 --> 00:47:55,806
[There Is A New Madeleine]

916
00:47:56,607 --> 00:48:00,378
[Bonjour Bokbunja Madeleine]

917
00:48:09,987 --> 00:48:11,021
[One...]

918
00:48:11,021 --> 00:48:12,456
[Two...]

919
00:48:13,224 --> 00:48:14,458
[Three!]

920
00:48:15,192 --> 00:48:17,128
[Checking Balance]

921
00:48:31,375 --> 00:48:33,577
[Putting It Safely Back In His Pocket]

922
00:48:34,011 --> 00:48:35,179
[Looks Around]

923
00:48:38,582 --> 00:48:41,318
[For The Customer Who Doesn't Drink Coffee]

924
00:48:41,318 --> 00:48:44,155
[She Collects Some Hot Water]

925
00:48:54,298 --> 00:48:58,302
Sir, this tea is on the house.

926
00:48:58,302 --> 00:49:00,087
Drink it while it's warm.

927
00:49:01,372 --> 00:49:03,774
- You're paying me already?
- Yes.

928
00:49:03,774 --> 00:49:05,643
Thank you.

929
00:49:05,643 --> 00:49:08,379
Why didn't you come with your wife?

930
00:49:08,379 --> 00:49:10,448
She can't come because she's over there...

931
00:49:10,448 --> 00:49:11,749
She's working?

932
00:49:11,749 --> 00:49:13,484
No, she's with my son.

933
00:49:13,484 --> 00:49:16,887
- She's unwell.
- I see.

934
00:49:16,887 --> 00:49:18,456
Oh, dear.

935
00:49:18,456 --> 00:49:21,425
You can eat this first,
and drink this when it cools down.

936
00:49:21,425 --> 00:49:24,195
- It's too hot right now.
- Okay.

937
00:49:24,195 --> 00:49:27,198
- Is this for my hands?
- Yes, you can use it for your hands.

938
00:49:28,499 --> 00:49:30,901
- How old are you, sir?
- What?

939
00:49:30,901 --> 00:49:32,703
How old are you?

940
00:49:32,703 --> 00:49:34,271
I'm 94 years old.

941
00:49:34,271 --> 00:49:35,739
My goodness.

942
00:49:35,739 --> 00:49:37,575
I live right up there.

943
00:49:37,575 --> 00:49:39,176
I see.

944
00:49:41,178 --> 00:49:42,913
[His House Is Located]

945
00:49:42,913 --> 00:49:46,183
[Right Behind Bonjour Bakery]

946
00:49:47,845 --> 00:49:52,015
[A Familiar Neighbor
Who Walked Past Regularly]

947
00:49:54,492 --> 00:49:57,428
[Took The Time To Visit Our Bakery]

948
00:50:08,639 --> 00:50:11,542
[Chamomile Tea Made By Hee Ae]

949
00:50:14,044 --> 00:50:16,313
[He Stirs It With His Fork
And Is About To Take A Sip When...]

950
00:50:16,313 --> 00:50:19,416
Drink this when it cools down.
It's too hot right now.

951
00:50:20,484 --> 00:50:22,720
[Let's Wait A Little]

952
00:50:28,025 --> 00:50:30,027
[Takes A Big Bite]

953
00:50:37,701 --> 00:50:39,570
[Let's Try The Tea Again]

954
00:50:40,871 --> 00:50:43,407
[He Strains The Tea Bag With One Hand]

955
00:50:45,609 --> 00:50:47,778
[Squeeze]

956
00:50:47,778 --> 00:50:50,514
[He Presses It Firmly]

957
00:50:51,282 --> 00:50:54,184
[For A Nice Strong Brew]

958
00:51:05,663 --> 00:51:08,732
[He Takes A Nice Warm Sip Of Chamomile Tea]

959
00:51:09,500 --> 00:51:12,736
[Reaches For Another Bite Of The Madeleine]

960
00:51:31,589 --> 00:51:35,092
[A Gentleman Who Can Take The Time
To Stop And Admire The Flowers]

961
00:51:39,563 --> 00:51:41,799
- Here's your change.
- Okay.

962
00:51:41,799 --> 00:51:43,000
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

963
00:51:43,500 --> 00:51:45,369
Hey, Seon Ho.

964
00:51:45,369 --> 00:51:48,639
That gentleman lives behind the bakery.

965
00:51:48,639 --> 00:51:50,641
His wife is too sick to come here, so...

966
00:51:53,077 --> 00:51:55,646
[She Suggests An Idea]

967
00:51:55,646 --> 00:51:56,814
It's over here.

968
00:51:58,949 --> 00:52:01,885
- Let's put together an assortment.
- I will.

969
00:52:03,354 --> 00:52:05,756
Yes, that's good.
That's a nice arrangement.

970
00:52:06,724 --> 00:52:09,493
[He Wraps Up A Selection Of Baked Goods]

971
00:52:09,493 --> 00:52:11,261
[And Places It Inside A Canvas Bag]

972
00:52:11,862 --> 00:52:13,230
[Glances Over]

973
00:52:14,298 --> 00:52:15,866
[Meanwhile]

974
00:52:15,866 --> 00:52:17,334
Are you finished?

975
00:52:17,334 --> 00:52:19,336
[The Customers Line Up To Pay]

976
00:52:22,139 --> 00:52:24,074
Hello.

977
00:52:24,074 --> 00:52:26,143
What a stylish gentleman.

978
00:52:26,143 --> 00:52:28,579
- What?
- You're very stylish, sir.

979
00:52:28,579 --> 00:52:29,947
Right.

980
00:52:29,947 --> 00:52:32,149
[Slurp]

981
00:52:32,149 --> 00:52:33,317
All right.

982
00:52:40,624 --> 00:52:42,429
- Make sure to check the receipt.
- I will.

983
00:52:42,429 --> 00:52:45,465
[The Customers Leave In A Flash]
Thank you.

984
00:52:46,438 --> 00:52:48,499
Oh, sir. Wait a minute. Wait one moment.

985
00:52:48,499 --> 00:52:51,535
Hee Ae, ring this loaf up for Table Five.

986
00:52:51,535 --> 00:52:53,897
- Table Five? Would you like to pay now?
- Yes.

987
00:52:53,897 --> 00:52:56,206
[While Hee Ae Handles The Register]

988
00:52:56,206 --> 00:52:57,546
Sir!

989
00:52:59,677 --> 00:53:00,978
Sir.

990
00:53:00,978 --> 00:53:04,114
- This is a gift for you.
- Thank you.

991
00:53:04,114 --> 00:53:06,116
Make sure to give it to your wife.

992
00:53:06,116 --> 00:53:07,851
- Have this with her.
- All right.

993
00:53:07,851 --> 00:53:09,253
- Yes.
- All right.

994
00:53:09,253 --> 00:53:11,822
- Thank you for coming.
- Thank you.

995
00:53:11,822 --> 00:53:13,264
All right.

996
00:53:20,097 --> 00:53:24,168
[The Voices]

997
00:53:24,168 --> 00:53:28,305
[Of The Customers]

998
00:53:31,809 --> 00:53:33,077
Could you pass it over?

999
00:53:33,077 --> 00:53:35,045
[Han Hong Sun, Park Heon Gu]

1000
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:36,680
She can't go outside.

1001
00:53:36,680 --> 00:53:39,149
- My legs hurt too much.
- Her legs hurt.

1002
00:53:39,149 --> 00:53:41,618
I heard they had rice cake sticks,
so I went to check it out.

1003
00:53:41,618 --> 00:53:45,489
Someone said they sold rice cake sticks.

1004
00:53:45,489 --> 00:53:49,227
He went to the Village Hall yesterday,
and someone there told him.

1005
00:53:52,663 --> 00:53:55,933
It's very light and sweet.

1006
00:53:55,933 --> 00:53:58,769
They said it's bokbunja bread.

1007
00:53:58,769 --> 00:54:01,939
I've never tried anything like it before.

1008
00:54:09,413 --> 00:54:10,914
Yes, it's me.

1009
00:54:10,914 --> 00:54:12,483
- Hi, Dad.
- Hi.

1010
00:54:12,483 --> 00:54:14,618
Are you free?

1011
00:54:14,618 --> 00:54:17,054
That's why I called you.
I'm on my lunch break.

1012
00:54:17,054 --> 00:54:18,922
I wanted to hear your voice.

1013
00:54:18,922 --> 00:54:20,824
How was it? Did you have a nice time?

1014
00:54:20,824 --> 00:54:22,292
Yes, what about you?

1015
00:54:22,292 --> 00:54:23,727
[Laughter]

1016
00:54:23,727 --> 00:54:25,629
- You had fun?
- Yes.

1017
00:54:25,629 --> 00:54:27,664
You and Mom are getting along, right?

1018
00:54:27,664 --> 00:54:29,433
Of course.

1019
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:30,868
Be good to her, okay?

1020
00:54:30,868 --> 00:54:32,369
You'd be lost without her.

1021
00:54:32,369 --> 00:54:34,371
Okay, bye.

1022
00:54:34,371 --> 00:54:37,875
What do you mean by "bye"?
Don't you and Mom want to hear my voice?

1023
00:54:37,875 --> 00:54:39,042
You don't need your kids.

1024
00:54:39,042 --> 00:54:40,511
You just need each other.

1025
00:54:40,511 --> 00:54:41,578
All right.

1026
00:54:41,578 --> 00:54:42,780
Get some rest.

1027
00:54:42,780 --> 00:54:44,648
All right. Bye.

1028
00:54:44,648 --> 00:54:46,250
Bye. I love you.

1029
00:54:46,250 --> 00:54:47,508
All right.

1030
00:54:51,789 --> 00:54:53,056
[Meanwhile In The Kitchen]

1031
00:54:53,056 --> 00:54:56,827
[Washing And Prepping Ingredients
For The Afternoon Menu]

1032
00:54:57,561 --> 00:54:58,896
[Rustle]

1033
00:55:00,030 --> 00:55:01,298
[Rustle]

1034
00:55:02,466 --> 00:55:05,302
[The Perfect Afternoon Dessert
Is Slowly Coming Together]

1035
00:55:06,837 --> 00:55:08,238
[Hint 1]

1036
00:55:08,238 --> 00:55:09,606
[Basil]

1037
00:55:10,407 --> 00:55:12,609
[Hint 2]

1038
00:55:12,609 --> 00:55:15,379
[Gochang's Representative Flower]

1039
00:55:16,947 --> 00:55:19,783
[Hint 3]

1040
00:55:19,783 --> 00:55:22,786
[Tomato]

1041
00:55:22,786 --> 00:55:26,023
[Afternoon Dessert Prep]

1042
00:55:26,023 --> 00:55:29,326
[Cut An X Into The Tomato]

1043
00:55:30,093 --> 00:55:33,497
[The Tomatoes Are Ready For Blanching]

1044
00:55:33,997 --> 00:55:37,935
[Waiting For The Water To Boil]

1045
00:55:39,002 --> 00:55:41,839
This is so boring.

1046
00:55:41,839 --> 00:55:44,241
[He Likes To Move Quickly]
This is really boring.

1047
00:55:44,241 --> 00:55:47,611
- I know you can't rush the basics but...
- Yes.

1048
00:55:47,611 --> 00:55:50,047
[He Smiles Like This When He's Restless]

1049
00:55:52,616 --> 00:55:54,318
It's double-bladed.

1050
00:55:57,321 --> 00:55:59,056
I really like this knife.

1051
00:55:59,056 --> 00:56:01,124
Not only does it have a good grip,

1052
00:56:01,758 --> 00:56:03,493
but it's also easy to use.

1053
00:56:03,493 --> 00:56:05,662
- I really like this knife.
- Why?

1054
00:56:05,662 --> 00:56:06,730
Because it's...

1055
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:08,198
[Seon Ho Pops His Head Into The Kitchen]

1056
00:56:08,198 --> 00:56:09,933
It's also easy to use.

1057
00:56:09,933 --> 00:56:12,703
[Explaining About The Knife]
It's great in a lot of ways.

1058
00:56:12,703 --> 00:56:14,872
[He's Not Interested In This Topic]

1059
00:56:17,841 --> 00:56:20,911
[The Perfect Dessert
Blanch The Sliced Tomatoes]

1060
00:56:20,911 --> 00:56:23,914
[Then Peel Off The Skin]

1061
00:56:26,683 --> 00:56:29,019
It's fun because they peel so easily.

1062
00:56:33,957 --> 00:56:36,393
Nothing happened.

1063
00:56:36,393 --> 00:56:38,662
- I told you to watch it, didn't I?
- Yes.

1064
00:56:38,662 --> 00:56:40,731
You need to stay alert in the kitchen.

1065
00:56:40,731 --> 00:56:42,566
Keep it together!

1066
00:56:42,566 --> 00:56:43,934
- Yes, sir.
- Not in here.

1067
00:56:43,934 --> 00:56:45,402
Ki Taek, are you getting scolded?

1068
00:56:45,402 --> 00:56:46,303
[He's Interested In This Topic]

1069
00:56:46,303 --> 00:56:47,971
- No.
- He got yelled at, right?

1070
00:56:47,971 --> 00:56:49,973
He keeps losing focus.

1071
00:56:49,973 --> 00:56:51,742
He dropped the tomato.

1072
00:56:51,742 --> 00:56:53,410
You rascal!

1073
00:56:53,410 --> 00:56:54,444
[Back To Work]

1074
00:56:54,444 --> 00:56:56,446
[Cut The Tomato In Half]

1075
00:56:58,621 --> 00:56:59,716
There it is.

1076
00:56:59,716 --> 00:57:02,753
[You Must Avoid The Stem]

1077
00:57:02,753 --> 00:57:05,155
[For Easier Removal Of The Stem And Seeds]
That's okay.

1078
00:57:05,155 --> 00:57:07,057
- You're doing okay.
- All right.

1079
00:57:07,057 --> 00:57:09,793
- It's such intricate work.
- Of course.

1080
00:57:10,427 --> 00:57:12,429
You're doing great, Ki Taek.

1081
00:57:12,429 --> 00:57:15,165
- That's impressive.
- He knows what he's doing.

1082
00:57:15,165 --> 00:57:17,567
You must feel nervous
with Seung Won watching.

1083
00:57:17,567 --> 00:57:18,936
I don't have tremors,

1084
00:57:18,936 --> 00:57:20,170
- but my hands are shaking.
- Really?

1085
00:57:20,170 --> 00:57:21,305
When I'm in here...

1086
00:57:21,305 --> 00:57:24,007
Take some medicine!

1087
00:57:24,007 --> 00:57:25,342
[Touching Advice]
Why blame me?

1088
00:57:25,342 --> 00:57:27,577
There are pills to fix that.

1089
00:57:27,577 --> 00:57:29,427
- Let's do it together.
- Okay.

1090
00:57:30,147 --> 00:57:31,148
[Handling It Like A Pro]

1091
00:57:35,352 --> 00:57:36,586
[Follows His Example]

1092
00:57:36,586 --> 00:57:38,455
You hold it like this, then...

1093
00:57:38,455 --> 00:57:39,656
That's it. Right there.

1094
00:57:39,656 --> 00:57:40,791
Like this.

1095
00:57:40,791 --> 00:57:42,059
[After Removing The Stem And Seeds]

1096
00:57:42,059 --> 00:57:46,229
[Simmer The Tomatoes In Sweet Syrup]

1097
00:57:46,229 --> 00:57:48,165
[Lay Them Out In An Oven-Safe Mold]

1098
00:57:49,099 --> 00:57:51,301
[Dry Them In The Oven For 4 Hours]

1099
00:57:52,903 --> 00:57:55,439
[Watch Them Bloom Into "Gochang's Flower"]

1100
00:57:57,541 --> 00:57:59,109
[See You In The Afternoon!]

1101
00:57:59,109 --> 00:58:01,345
[1:10 p.m]

1102
00:58:03,413 --> 00:58:06,850
[The Hall Team Is Busy Cleaning Up]

1103
00:58:08,919 --> 00:58:10,187
- Your back must hurt.
- I'm okay.

1104
00:58:10,187 --> 00:58:13,346
For a tall guy like you,
washing dishes can't be easy.

1105
00:58:14,257 --> 00:58:16,293
[Peeking Out]

1106
00:58:16,293 --> 00:58:19,196
- Is everyone okay?
- How did you do this yesterday?

1107
00:58:19,196 --> 00:58:21,431
Yesterday was so tough.

1108
00:58:21,431 --> 00:58:22,532
It really was.

1109
00:58:22,532 --> 00:58:26,970
- But you two must make a good team.
- Why's that?

1110
00:58:26,970 --> 00:58:29,973
It doesn't seem hectic here at all.

1111
00:58:31,174 --> 00:58:33,343
Really? I felt like a mess.

1112
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:35,312
I even spilled stuff. It was chaos.

1113
00:58:37,080 --> 00:58:39,416
[Coffee Spillage]
I put in some jam.

1114
00:58:39,416 --> 00:58:41,284
This area is off-limits.

1115
00:58:41,284 --> 00:58:43,286
[Hot Water Overflowing]
Sorry.

1116
00:58:44,321 --> 00:58:45,389
[Accident-Prone]

1117
00:58:45,389 --> 00:58:47,257
I messed up.

1118
00:58:47,257 --> 00:58:48,325
Just don't get hurt.

1119
00:58:48,325 --> 00:58:49,893
Yes, I'll be careful.

1120
00:58:49,893 --> 00:58:52,896
[Bonjour Bakery]

1121
00:58:53,430 --> 00:58:56,166
We picked up our strawberries from him.

1122
00:58:56,166 --> 00:58:58,902
- Oh, he's from the strawberry farm?
- Yes.

1123
00:58:58,902 --> 00:59:01,371
[A Familiar Face Has Arrived]

1124
00:59:01,371 --> 00:59:02,339
Hello.

1125
00:59:02,339 --> 00:59:04,808
- Hello.
- Hello!

1126
00:59:04,808 --> 00:59:06,410
- Hello.
- Hello.

1127
00:59:06,410 --> 00:59:07,811
[The Strawberry Farm Owner And His Family]
Hello.

1128
00:59:07,811 --> 00:59:09,546
[Presents Her ID]
You've got your ID ready!

1129
00:59:09,546 --> 00:59:11,281
- Your ID.
- You must be over 65 years old.

1130
00:59:11,281 --> 00:59:13,784
- Yes.
- Three people? Take a seat over there.

1131
00:59:13,784 --> 00:59:14,851
Thank you.

1132
00:59:14,851 --> 00:59:16,286
[Strawberry Farm Owner Lee Jong Heon]

1133
00:59:16,286 --> 00:59:17,687
[Jong Hyeon's Mother Bae Dong Sim]

1134
00:59:17,687 --> 00:59:19,089
[Strawberry Farm Owner
Nam Eun Sun]

1135
00:59:19,089 --> 00:59:20,891
"Bonjour Strawberry Éclair."

1136
00:59:20,891 --> 00:59:22,159
Those are my strawberries, right?

1137
00:59:22,159 --> 00:59:24,895
Yes, that's right. We really did use them.

1138
00:59:24,895 --> 00:59:26,430
"My strawberries."

1139
00:59:27,130 --> 00:59:30,133
He owns a strawberry farm,
so he'll probably go for the strawberries.

1140
00:59:31,034 --> 00:59:32,936
[Getting It Ready In Advance]

1141
00:59:32,936 --> 00:59:34,504
- I'll bring them to you.
- Yes, please.

1142
00:59:34,504 --> 00:59:36,006
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1143
00:59:38,175 --> 00:59:39,576
I'm guessing he wants the strawberries.

1144
00:59:39,576 --> 00:59:40,544
He wants two of those.

1145
00:59:40,544 --> 00:59:43,080
- So we need one more?
- Yes.

1146
00:59:43,647 --> 00:59:46,383
One more Strawberry Éclair, please!

1147
00:59:46,383 --> 00:59:47,451
Okay!

1148
00:59:48,418 --> 00:59:49,486
All right.

1149
00:59:52,148 --> 00:59:55,485
[He Gets To Have One That's Freshly Baked]

1150
00:59:55,992 --> 00:59:58,128
- I'll carry this plate.
- Okay.

1151
00:59:58,128 --> 00:59:59,496
Got it? Okay.

1152
00:59:59,496 --> 01:00:01,331
- Hello.
- Hello.

1153
01:00:01,331 --> 01:00:02,666
Hello.

1154
01:00:02,666 --> 01:00:05,335
[2 Éclairs, 1 Green Barley Tart]
We just made these this morning.

1155
01:00:05,969 --> 01:00:07,237
Are you the strawberry farm owner?

1156
01:00:07,237 --> 01:00:08,672
Yes, that's right.

1157
01:00:09,372 --> 01:00:11,007
The strawberries are so tasty.

1158
01:00:11,007 --> 01:00:12,527
Thank you.

1159
01:00:14,077 --> 01:00:15,445
[Click]

1160
01:00:17,681 --> 01:00:19,282
These are our strawberries?

1161
01:00:21,585 --> 01:00:24,921
[Reunited With His Strawberries
In Dessert Form]

1162
01:00:24,921 --> 01:00:27,524
We should try it
since they're our strawberries.

1163
01:00:28,859 --> 01:00:31,027
[Picks Up The Strawberry
They Grew Themselves]

1164
01:00:34,097 --> 01:00:35,232
Is it good?

1165
01:00:35,232 --> 01:00:37,801
- Those are your strawberries.
- Yes.

1166
01:00:37,801 --> 01:00:38,869
[A New Arrival To The Group]

1167
01:00:38,869 --> 01:00:40,604
- It's tasty.
- It's delicious.

1168
01:00:40,604 --> 01:00:43,540
[Their Acquaintances Take A Seat
At The Table Beside Them]

1169
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:44,608
[Gapyeong Village Chairwoman Ko Hyeon Mi]

1170
01:00:44,608 --> 01:00:45,909
[Town Chief Of Sillim-Myeon, Gochang
Ko Hyeon Gyu]

1171
01:00:45,909 --> 01:00:47,077
[Hwang Jin]

1172
01:00:47,077 --> 01:00:48,345
I love the smell of the freesia.

1173
01:00:48,345 --> 01:00:50,614
- What?
- The freesias smell so nice.

1174
01:00:50,614 --> 01:00:52,949
I told you. My husband...

1175
01:00:52,949 --> 01:00:54,718
I like freesias,

1176
01:00:54,718 --> 01:00:56,786
so he used to buy them for me,

1177
01:00:56,786 --> 01:00:58,788
but not anymore, even if I say,
"Freesias are so pretty!"

1178
01:00:58,788 --> 01:01:01,391
- Is it fresh flowers?
- Yes.

1179
01:01:01,391 --> 01:01:03,960
What do you want to drink?

1180
01:01:03,960 --> 01:01:05,962
[As For The Chairwoman...]

1181
01:01:05,962 --> 01:01:09,299
It's made of Gochang's local ingredients.

1182
01:01:09,299 --> 01:01:10,200
[Yesterday, Before Opening]

1183
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:12,002
It's made of real green barley.

1184
01:01:12,002 --> 01:01:15,338
[She Helped With The Menu Tasting]
Have a taste.

1185
01:01:15,338 --> 01:01:16,606
- How is it?
- It's delicious.

1186
01:01:16,606 --> 01:01:18,475
- It's tasty.
- Yes, it's good.

1187
01:01:18,475 --> 01:01:19,809
Hello again.

1188
01:01:20,277 --> 01:01:22,179
- You're here to help us out again?
- Yes.

1189
01:01:22,179 --> 01:01:24,447
- We're ready to order.
- Okay.

1190
01:01:24,447 --> 01:01:26,249
We want that dessert.

1191
01:01:26,249 --> 01:01:27,350
The strawberry one?

1192
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:28,552
- The Strawberry Éclair.
- Yes.

1193
01:01:28,552 --> 01:01:30,887
- The strawberries are fresh.
- We'll have one of those.

1194
01:01:30,887 --> 01:01:32,289
- As for the coffee...
- Latte?

1195
01:01:32,289 --> 01:01:34,057
- Two café latte?
- Café latte.

1196
01:01:34,057 --> 01:01:35,325
- Café latte?
- Yes.

1197
01:01:35,325 --> 01:01:37,561
[Even While Cleaning Up]
Café latte?

1198
01:01:37,561 --> 01:01:39,229
[Our Barista Hears Everything]
Latte...

1199
01:01:39,229 --> 01:01:40,397
- You want two, right?
- Yes.

1200
01:01:40,397 --> 01:01:42,866
- Two café lattes, please.
- Okay.

1201
01:01:42,866 --> 01:01:46,002
[He's Already Making Them]

1202
01:01:51,141 --> 01:01:54,411
[Steam The Milk Until The Pitcher Feels Hot]

1203
01:01:55,011 --> 01:01:57,247
[Be Sure To Clean It Afterwards]

1204
01:01:57,814 --> 01:01:59,614
[Finish With A Purge Spray To Prevent Backflow]

1205
01:02:00,584 --> 01:02:02,219
[Freshly Extracted Espresso Shot]

1206
01:02:12,529 --> 01:02:14,631
[A Casually Drawn Heart]

1207
01:02:16,333 --> 01:02:18,268
- You keep getting better.
- I keep improving,

1208
01:02:18,268 --> 01:02:20,270
- don't you think?
- Yes.

1209
01:02:23,206 --> 01:02:24,441
As of yet,

1210
01:02:24,441 --> 01:02:26,209
the coffee tastes good,

1211
01:02:26,209 --> 01:02:27,510
but my latte art is...

1212
01:02:27,510 --> 01:02:30,013
- Is it a leaf?
- It's a bit clumsy, isn't it?

1213
01:02:30,013 --> 01:02:32,015
- It's a bit...
- The heart is a bit...

1214
01:02:32,015 --> 01:02:33,283
It's lacking a little love.

1215
01:02:33,283 --> 01:02:34,818
The heart?

1216
01:02:34,818 --> 01:02:36,553
I'll try to make it bigger next time.

1217
01:02:36,553 --> 01:02:38,197
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1218
01:02:40,123 --> 01:02:41,258
It's tasty.

1219
01:02:41,258 --> 01:02:43,093
- It's tasty!
- Is it?

1220
01:02:43,093 --> 01:02:44,427
- I did well, right?
- Yes.

1221
01:02:47,063 --> 01:02:48,498
[Seon Ho's Latte Is Overjoyed]

1222
01:02:48,498 --> 01:02:51,935
[With The Sweet Strawberry Éclair]

1223
01:02:52,535 --> 01:02:54,938
- What are these?
- It's tasty.

1224
01:02:54,938 --> 01:02:57,374
- Is it a peanut?
- Some kind of nut.

1225
01:02:57,374 --> 01:02:59,609
[Eats It Off The Knife]

1226
01:03:00,910 --> 01:03:02,012
It's nutty.

1227
01:03:02,579 --> 01:03:03,747
It tastes like a peanut.

1228
01:03:03,747 --> 01:03:05,682
- What is this?
- It's not a peanut.

1229
01:03:05,682 --> 01:03:07,250
Is it chocolate?

1230
01:03:07,250 --> 01:03:08,852
That's not it, either.

1231
01:03:09,552 --> 01:03:10,920
[Embedded Like Small Gems]

1232
01:03:10,920 --> 01:03:13,056
[Roasted Hazelnuts]

1233
01:03:13,957 --> 01:03:17,327
[The Secret To Its Crunchy Texture
And Nutty Aroma]

1234
01:03:18,962 --> 01:03:20,964
[Start With A Bite Of The Fragrant Hazelnut]

1235
01:03:20,964 --> 01:03:22,899
[Then Split The Strawberry In Half]

1236
01:03:24,234 --> 01:03:25,669
[Sweet And Refreshing]

1237
01:03:25,669 --> 01:03:27,003
They're talking about it.

1238
01:03:28,805 --> 01:03:30,307
- Aren't the strawberries good?
- Great job.

1239
01:03:30,307 --> 01:03:32,475
- They're great.
- We had them all.

1240
01:03:33,710 --> 01:03:35,045
He's so pleased with himself.

1241
01:03:35,045 --> 01:03:37,647
He won't stop boasting about them.

1242
01:03:39,015 --> 01:03:40,583
The strawberries are great.

1243
01:03:40,583 --> 01:03:42,919
- You admitted it was good.
- Yes, I did.

1244
01:03:42,919 --> 01:03:45,155
- You said they were tasty.
- I had more when I got back

1245
01:03:45,155 --> 01:03:46,556
because they were so tasty.

1246
01:03:47,123 --> 01:03:51,428
If you eat a strawberry down to the stem,

1247
01:03:51,428 --> 01:03:53,563
it means a lot to us farmers.

1248
01:03:53,563 --> 01:03:55,298
We appreciate it

1249
01:03:55,298 --> 01:03:58,435
because most people leave
the white bit at the end.

1250
01:03:58,435 --> 01:04:01,004
But you ate it all the way to the stem,

1251
01:04:01,004 --> 01:04:02,672
- so I was really grateful.
- Really?

1252
01:04:02,672 --> 01:04:06,543
[From Now On]

1253
01:04:06,543 --> 01:04:10,747
[Eat Strawberries Like Seon Ho]

1254
01:04:10,747 --> 01:04:13,149
That matters a lot to farmers.

1255
01:04:13,149 --> 01:04:16,453
They appreciate it
when you enjoy their product.

1256
01:04:16,453 --> 01:04:18,855
We're the ones who are grateful.

1257
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:22,192
What's the best way to wash strawberries?

1258
01:04:22,192 --> 01:04:23,460
Before you eat them.

1259
01:04:23,460 --> 01:04:25,862
It's best to eat them just as they are.

1260
01:04:25,862 --> 01:04:27,330
Yes, I've heard some farmers

1261
01:04:27,330 --> 01:04:31,634
- don't use a lot of pesticides.
- We don't use that many pesticides.

1262
01:04:31,634 --> 01:04:33,303
- They also break down.
- Yes.

1263
01:04:33,303 --> 01:04:35,472
And domestic regulations are quite strict.

1264
01:04:35,472 --> 01:04:37,874
So, if the pesticide level is too high,

1265
01:04:37,874 --> 01:04:40,377
- we can face serious consequences.
- We can suffer a huge loss.

1266
01:04:40,377 --> 01:04:43,046
I recommend not washing them.

1267
01:04:43,046 --> 01:04:44,447
But a lot of people

1268
01:04:44,447 --> 01:04:46,516
- use baking soda, salt, and vinegar.
- Yes.

1269
01:04:46,516 --> 01:04:48,985
- And they take the stems off.
- They do.

1270
01:04:48,985 --> 01:04:50,653
- But it's not necessary?
- That's right.

1271
01:04:50,653 --> 01:04:53,323
They can gather dust
while they're being transported.

1272
01:04:53,323 --> 01:04:55,392
- That's true.
- Just rinse them off with clean water.

1273
01:04:55,392 --> 01:04:58,795
- Give them a quick rinse just once.
- That's what I recommend.

1274
01:04:58,795 --> 01:05:00,563
It's best to eat it by holding the stem.

1275
01:05:00,563 --> 01:05:03,266
- Yes.
- In one bite.

1276
01:05:03,266 --> 01:05:04,267
[Gochang Strawberries]

1277
01:05:07,537 --> 01:05:10,940
[20 Minutes Before Break Time]

1278
01:05:13,176 --> 01:05:14,511
[Day 2 Morning]

1279
01:05:14,511 --> 01:05:16,379
It's risen already.

1280
01:05:16,379 --> 01:05:18,515
This was really thick and sticky.

1281
01:05:18,515 --> 01:05:22,252
[Bonjour Bakery's Chef Cha]

1282
01:05:23,553 --> 01:05:26,222
[5 Desserts And 3 Baked Goods
For The Morning Menu]

1283
01:05:26,222 --> 01:05:27,624
[And 1 Bread]
Sorry.

1284
01:05:27,624 --> 01:05:29,259
[Baked A Total Of 9 Items]

1285
01:05:30,660 --> 01:05:32,495
Take all the cameras outside.

1286
01:05:34,397 --> 01:05:39,769
[Without Stepping Out Even For A Moment]

1287
01:05:42,238 --> 01:05:44,541
[On Top Of That]

1288
01:05:44,541 --> 01:05:47,610
[He's Been Hunched Over All Morning]

1289
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:55,051
[Casually Heading Somewhere...]

1290
01:05:55,752 --> 01:05:59,756
[It's The Staff Break Room]

1291
01:06:01,024 --> 01:06:02,992
I expect Seung Won
will whip up something good.

1292
01:06:02,992 --> 01:06:06,930
[Once Again, He Prepares Lunch]

1293
01:06:08,832 --> 01:06:13,736
[For The Bonjour Bakery Family]

1294
01:06:13,736 --> 01:06:16,739
[The Hall Is Filled With People]

1295
01:06:19,242 --> 01:06:21,110
[One Spoon Of Soybean Paste]

1296
01:06:23,680 --> 01:06:25,815
[Two Spoons]

1297
01:06:29,152 --> 01:06:33,289
[Mix In Some Gochujang]

1298
01:06:33,823 --> 01:06:35,325
[Add Some Red Pepper Powder]

1299
01:06:44,267 --> 01:06:47,737
[Rummaging Around]

1300
01:06:50,507 --> 01:06:53,109
[Takes Out Meat And Vegetables
From The Fridge]

1301
01:07:00,517 --> 01:07:03,286
[Slice The Vegetables]

1302
01:07:04,287 --> 01:07:05,955
[Add Some Scallion]

1303
01:07:05,955 --> 01:07:08,358
Is that beef?

1304
01:07:08,892 --> 01:07:12,228
Today's lunch is soybean paste stew.

1305
01:07:12,228 --> 01:07:13,496
Beef soybean paste stew.

1306
01:07:13,496 --> 01:07:15,519
[Today's Lunch Is Beef Soybean Paste Stew]

1307
01:07:28,978 --> 01:07:33,216
[While Waiting For The Flavor To Deepen]

1308
01:07:33,216 --> 01:07:34,617
That's done.

1309
01:07:34,617 --> 01:07:36,519
Now, I'm going to make...

1310
01:07:36,519 --> 01:07:41,324
[Some Side Dishes To Pair With The Stew]

1311
01:07:41,324 --> 01:07:47,063
[Ham Sizzling To A Nice Golden Brown]

1312
01:08:12,422 --> 01:08:14,657
- Ki Taek.
- Yes?

1313
01:08:14,657 --> 01:08:17,160
Let's start heating up the rice.

1314
01:08:17,160 --> 01:08:20,296
Otoki makes it so nice and easy.

1315
01:08:20,296 --> 01:08:21,296
Yes.

1316
01:08:21,831 --> 01:08:23,399
[Instant Rice Ready To Go]
This is so convenient.

1317
01:08:23,399 --> 01:08:27,103
[Konjac White Rice]

1318
01:08:31,608 --> 01:08:33,543
Use that to keep the lids sealed.

1319
01:08:34,844 --> 01:08:35,844
That's it.

1320
01:08:38,615 --> 01:08:43,786
[The Table Is Set For The Staff Lunch]

1321
01:08:44,454 --> 01:08:46,789
- Thank you.
- Thank you for coming.

1322
01:08:46,789 --> 01:08:48,458
[The Customers Return Home]
Thank you.

1323
01:08:48,458 --> 01:08:50,059
Thank you.

1324
01:09:01,371 --> 01:09:04,307
[On Break]

1325
01:09:05,174 --> 01:09:07,487
- Come and eat, Hee Ae.
- Okay.

1326
01:09:08,544 --> 01:09:10,146
Let's eat!

1327
01:09:10,146 --> 01:09:13,750
[Break Time - 2 p.m. To 3 p.m.]

1328
01:09:13,750 --> 01:09:15,284
Wow, it looks so good.

1329
01:09:15,752 --> 01:09:16,953
Look at those eggs!

1330
01:09:19,956 --> 01:09:21,524
- What is all this?
- I'm so impressed.

1331
01:09:21,524 --> 01:09:23,626
- Come quickly.
- This is unbelievable.

1332
01:09:23,626 --> 01:09:26,129
A [Homemade Meal By Chef Cha]
It looks so tasty.

1333
01:09:26,129 --> 01:09:27,897
[We Need To Take A Photo]
It's such a rare privilege.

1334
01:09:27,897 --> 01:09:29,866
You're so right.

1335
01:09:29,866 --> 01:09:31,067
- This is crazy.
- Let's eat.

1336
01:09:34,437 --> 01:09:36,817
- My mouth is watering.
- Thank you.

1337
01:09:38,341 --> 01:09:39,509
- Ki Taek.
- Yes?

1338
01:09:39,509 --> 01:09:40,877
This is for you.

1339
01:09:40,877 --> 01:09:42,045
Thank you.

1340
01:09:42,045 --> 01:09:47,050
The stew looks like it's full of flavor.

1341
01:09:48,351 --> 01:09:49,452
- Eat up.
- Thank you.

1342
01:09:49,452 --> 01:09:51,154
- Let's eat.
- Thank you!

1343
01:09:51,154 --> 01:09:52,689
Great job in the hall today.

1344
01:09:52,689 --> 01:09:55,425
Seon Ho looks exhausted.

1345
01:09:55,425 --> 01:09:57,308
Seon Ho looks exhausted.

1346
01:10:01,431 --> 01:10:06,836
[Trying The Soybean Paste Stew First]

1347
01:10:06,836 --> 01:10:08,304
- How is it?
- It's amazing.

1348
01:10:08,304 --> 01:10:09,972
- Is it amazing?
- Really?

1349
01:10:22,852 --> 01:10:24,187
Scoop the stuff at the bottom.

1350
01:10:34,964 --> 01:10:36,566
[A Bite Of The Irresistible Ham]

1351
01:10:36,566 --> 01:10:38,034
The ham also tastes amazing.

1352
01:10:49,679 --> 01:10:50,747
Hee Ae.

1353
01:10:50,747 --> 01:10:51,781
[Have Some Eggs]

1354
01:10:51,781 --> 01:10:52,849
Thank you.

1355
01:10:52,849 --> 01:10:55,184
- These eggs...
- Choose the ones on top or bottom.

1356
01:10:55,184 --> 01:10:56,919
- Take two.
- I'll take this one.

1357
01:10:56,919 --> 01:10:58,788
- We get two?
- Yes, two each.

1358
01:10:59,489 --> 01:11:00,656
- Take two.
- What a luxury.

1359
01:11:00,656 --> 01:11:02,058
- Two?
- That's...

1360
01:11:02,058 --> 01:11:03,626
- Hee Ae.
- Yes?

1361
01:11:03,626 --> 01:11:05,228
I heard you made poached eggs yesterday.

1362
01:11:06,162 --> 01:11:08,431
- Forget what you heard.
- I wish I had tried it.

1363
01:11:08,431 --> 01:11:09,766
Forget what you heard.

1364
01:11:09,766 --> 01:11:12,502
What was I thinking,
cooking in front of Chef Cha?

1365
01:11:12,502 --> 01:11:14,704
What a joke.

1366
01:11:14,704 --> 01:11:17,206
I enjoyed them, though.

1367
01:11:17,974 --> 01:11:19,041
It was great.

1368
01:11:19,041 --> 01:11:21,043
Wipe it from your mind.

1369
01:11:21,477 --> 01:11:23,279
After a hearty meal like this,

1370
01:11:23,279 --> 01:11:24,614
when we get back to work,

1371
01:11:24,614 --> 01:11:25,748
- I agree.
- I feel recharged.

1372
01:11:25,748 --> 01:11:26,716
- Really?
- Yes.

1373
01:11:26,716 --> 01:11:29,118
I ate so much for lunch yesterday,

1374
01:11:29,118 --> 01:11:30,386
and I burned it all off.

1375
01:11:30,386 --> 01:11:32,655
- Of course.
- I'd be in trouble if I didn't eat.

1376
01:11:32,655 --> 01:11:34,994
- We need a solid meal.
- Yes.

1377
01:11:38,528 --> 01:11:41,297
[From Now On]

1378
01:11:41,297 --> 01:11:44,700
[We'll Try To Have Hearty Meals]

1379
01:11:45,701 --> 01:11:49,038
[So That We Can Greet]

1380
01:11:49,038 --> 01:11:53,714
[Even More Customers]

1381
01:11:53,714 --> 01:11:55,344
Does it taste okay?

1382
01:11:55,344 --> 01:11:57,313
It's incredible.

1383
01:11:57,313 --> 01:11:59,209
It's so good.

1384
01:12:01,350 --> 01:12:07,190
It's nice to share meals like this.

1385
01:12:07,190 --> 01:12:09,492
- Isn't that right?
- Yes.

1386
01:12:09,492 --> 01:12:12,161
We've known each other for so long,

1387
01:12:12,161 --> 01:12:13,729
but we haven't eaten together.

1388
01:12:13,729 --> 01:12:15,307
- Right?
- But I feel so comfortable.

1389
01:12:15,307 --> 01:12:16,332
Really?

1390
01:12:16,332 --> 01:12:19,735
When I eat with other people,

1391
01:12:19,735 --> 01:12:21,504
- You get uncomfortable?
- If I feel uneasy,

1392
01:12:21,504 --> 01:12:23,372
I always get indigestion.

1393
01:12:23,372 --> 01:12:25,208
I get affected really easily.

1394
01:12:25,208 --> 01:12:26,342
[I See]

1395
01:12:26,342 --> 01:12:29,912
But I feel so comfortable right now.

1396
01:12:29,912 --> 01:12:31,981
It's a relief you feel that way.

1397
01:12:31,981 --> 01:12:33,950
I didn't realize you were like that.

1398
01:12:33,950 --> 01:12:35,551
- That was a great meal.
- Thank you.

1399
01:12:35,551 --> 01:12:37,386
You can just leave them.

1400
01:12:37,386 --> 01:12:39,322
- Let's do this.
- Yes, let's do this.

1401
01:12:39,322 --> 01:12:40,882
[Now That We've Eaten, Let's Keep Going]

1402
01:12:41,557 --> 01:12:44,560
[2:55 p.m.]

1403
01:12:48,097 --> 01:12:52,768
[Bonjour Bakery Day 2 Afternoon,
Open For Business]

1404
01:12:53,169 --> 01:12:54,737
Who had it?

1405
01:12:54,737 --> 01:12:57,144
The Camellia Tart?
The people on the far right.

1406
01:12:57,144 --> 01:13:01,008
The mother and daughter at the far end.

1407
01:13:02,311 --> 01:13:05,915
[Curious]

1408
01:13:07,216 --> 01:13:09,118
- They loved it.
- Really?

1409
01:13:09,118 --> 01:13:10,586
By the way,

1410
01:13:10,586 --> 01:13:12,054
- it's so pretty.
- Really?

1411
01:13:12,054 --> 01:13:13,556
[Fulfilled]
That's good to hear.

1412
01:13:15,625 --> 01:13:18,427
[Eager To See The Customers Reaction]
I see you had the Camellia Tart.

1413
01:13:18,427 --> 01:13:19,729
- How was it? Was it okay?
- Yes.

1414
01:13:19,729 --> 01:13:21,731
It was tasty and not too sweet.

1415
01:13:21,731 --> 01:13:24,166
- Hello.
- What did you think?

1416
01:13:24,166 --> 01:13:26,569
[Proudly Showing Off]
If you're drawn to pretty things,

1417
01:13:26,569 --> 01:13:28,371
[His Beautiful Creation]
I recommend the Camellia Tart.

1418
01:13:28,371 --> 01:13:30,840
[Chef Cha's Most Ambitious Work]
Oh, the Camellia Tart?

1419
01:13:30,840 --> 01:13:32,842
- It's very elegant.
- It was so well done.

1420
01:13:32,842 --> 01:13:35,177
It's the hardest to make.

1421
01:13:35,177 --> 01:13:37,413
- For various reasons...
- It was so interesting.

1422
01:13:37,413 --> 01:13:39,482
[It's Hard To Make But I Want To Sell More]

1423
01:13:39,482 --> 01:13:42,985
[Enough To Lift You Off The Chair]
I like this one.

1424
01:13:43,386 --> 01:13:46,188
[And Makes Your Eyes Light Up]
It's nice and chewy, isn't it?

1425
01:13:46,188 --> 01:13:48,758
We're finishing these too quickly.

1426
01:13:48,758 --> 01:13:51,894
[They're Gone In A Flash]

1427
01:13:51,894 --> 01:13:53,396
[Bonjour Bakery]

1428
01:13:53,396 --> 01:13:59,402
[Chef Cha's Beloved Dessert]

1429
01:14:00,102 --> 01:14:03,339
[Manager Hee Ae's Morning Routine]

1430
01:14:04,040 --> 01:14:05,574
[Haemongdang]

1431
01:14:05,574 --> 01:14:08,978
[6:30 a.m.]

1432
01:14:16,652 --> 01:14:21,123
[She's Intently Writing Something Down]

1433
01:14:30,137 --> 01:14:34,375
[Every Morning, I've Been
Studying English For Years]

1434
01:14:35,771 --> 01:14:39,675
[What Do I Do When I'm Done Studying?]

1435
01:14:40,180 --> 01:14:43,383
[I Make Myself A Simple Breakfast]

1436
01:14:45,014 --> 01:14:49,318
[Greek Yogurt]

1437
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:53,189
[Blueberries]

1438
01:14:53,189 --> 01:14:57,393
[Some Nuts]

1439
01:14:57,393 --> 01:15:00,930
[A Banana]

1440
01:15:00,930 --> 01:15:05,301
[Some Olive Oil]

1441
01:15:05,901 --> 01:15:09,005
[So Tasty]

1442
01:15:10,840 --> 01:15:15,244
[From Putting On My Hairband]

1443
01:15:18,948 --> 01:15:23,152
[To Putting On My Shoes]

1444
01:15:26,655 --> 01:15:31,193
[I Won't Miss A Single Step]
